1
00:00:11,980 --> 00:00:13,607
<i>My mother always says</i>

2
00:00:13,682 --> 00:00:15,741
<i>people are not fools.</i>

3
00:00:19,288 --> 00:00:20,414
<i>Nobody chooses the Devil.</i>

4
00:00:20,489 --> 00:00:22,457
<i>The Devil chooses you.</i>

5
00:00:22,524 --> 00:00:24,515
<i>Come on, come on,
let's talk about this!</i>

6
00:00:24,593 --> 00:00:27,460
Open the door
or I'll break it down!

7
00:00:27,529 --> 00:00:29,258
You're not gonna leave me, Patty!

8
00:00:29,331 --> 00:00:31,356
<i>He choose my mother
the day she was born.</i>

9
00:00:42,778 --> 00:00:45,007
<i>He didn't come
for her right away.</i>

10
00:00:45,547 --> 00:00:46,912
<i>The way I see it,</i>

11
00:00:46,982 --> 00:00:49,712
<i>he waited until Grandma Angie
gave in to her enraged father</i>

12
00:00:49,785 --> 00:00:52,379
<i>and abandoned her baby on the
steps of St. Peter's Cathedral.</i>

13
00:01:06,835 --> 00:01:10,327
<i>Actually, it was right after.</i>

14
00:01:13,108 --> 00:01:15,770
<i>When Grandma Angie
decided to keep my mother</i>

15
00:01:15,844 --> 00:01:18,074
<i>and wasn't allowed to come home.</i>

16
00:01:18,146 --> 00:01:20,979
<i>That's when he knew my mother
was ripe for the taking.</i>

17
00:01:21,049 --> 00:01:22,073
Here you go, folks.

18
00:01:22,150 --> 00:01:24,141
<i>All he had to do
was break her spirit.</i>

19
00:01:25,187 --> 00:01:29,521
<i>Turns out that wasn't so easy.</i>

20
00:01:29,591 --> 00:01:31,354
<i>No matter what he threw at her,</i>

21
00:01:31,426 --> 00:01:33,223
<i>she came back swinging.</i>

22
00:01:36,164 --> 00:01:38,098
We're late!

23
00:01:41,002 --> 00:01:44,335
<i>Grandma Angie says that's
because my mother is a genius.</i>

24
00:01:44,406 --> 00:01:47,933
<i>You find her a dumpster,
she'll make you a feast.</i>

25
00:01:48,009 --> 00:01:49,203
How'd it go?

26
00:01:51,613 --> 00:01:54,138
<i>So, growing a little impatient,</i>

27
00:01:54,216 --> 00:01:56,207
<i>the Devil changed his strategy.</i>

28
00:01:56,284 --> 00:01:59,048
This isn't a hotel, you know.

29
00:01:59,121 --> 00:02:00,554
I see you.

30
00:02:00,622 --> 00:02:02,988
Every night.

31
00:02:03,058 --> 00:02:04,218
Don't you got someplace to go?

32
00:02:04,292 --> 00:02:06,726
Are we under arrest?
No.

33
00:02:08,630 --> 00:02:10,325
I brought you dinner.

34
00:02:14,736 --> 00:02:18,763
<i>For the first time in her life,
something went right.</i>

35
00:02:18,840 --> 00:02:21,274
<i>Now, it wasn't Romeo and Juliet,</i>

36
00:02:21,343 --> 00:02:23,334
<i>but she was happy.</i>

37
00:02:23,412 --> 00:02:24,401
Hey, babe.

38
00:02:24,479 --> 00:02:25,844
<i>Joey was born, then me.</i>

39
00:02:25,914 --> 00:02:27,905
Hi.

40
00:02:30,886 --> 00:02:32,478
Is it good?

41
00:02:32,554 --> 00:02:33,646
Hot.
Ooh, that's good.

42
00:02:33,722 --> 00:02:35,656
<i>Careful.</i>

43
00:02:35,724 --> 00:02:37,191
You all right?

44
00:02:37,259 --> 00:02:38,521
Yeah, I'm okay, babe.

45
00:02:38,593 --> 00:02:40,959
I'm fine.

46
00:02:41,029 --> 00:02:43,623
<i>Then he knocked her flat.</i>

47
00:02:43,698 --> 00:02:45,689
Patty!

48
00:02:50,872 --> 00:02:54,933
<i>My father's cancer
took two years to kill him,</i>

49
00:02:55,010 --> 00:02:57,774
<i>and all their savings.</i>

50
00:03:02,284 --> 00:03:03,945
They towed the car.

51
00:03:04,019 --> 00:03:05,043
Do you believe it?

52
00:03:05,120 --> 00:03:07,111
And I couldn't even take the bus.

53
00:03:07,189 --> 00:03:08,816
The bus driver said
to me I didn't have

54
00:03:08,890 --> 00:03:10,983
enough change and I looked
at him and I said,

55
00:03:11,059 --> 00:03:12,185
"My husband just died.

56
00:03:12,260 --> 00:03:14,194
You can't give me a friggin' ride?"

57
00:03:14,262 --> 00:03:16,127
<i>That's when he showed up.</i>

58
00:03:16,198 --> 00:03:18,132
This is Mr. Russo.

59
00:03:18,200 --> 00:03:19,724
From the funeral parlor.

60
00:03:25,040 --> 00:03:28,271
Mrs. Montanari, we offer
three packages: Deluxe,

61
00:03:28,343 --> 00:03:31,904
Premium...

62
00:03:31,980 --> 00:03:34,141
and Beloved.

63
00:03:34,216 --> 00:03:36,844
Now, try not to think of them
as better or worse.

64
00:03:36,918 --> 00:03:38,010
Do I have to pick now?

65
00:03:38,086 --> 00:03:40,077
No, not at all.

66
00:03:40,155 --> 00:03:42,521
I'm here to make this
as painless as possible.

67
00:03:42,591 --> 00:03:43,956
If you'd like to call me,

68
00:03:44,025 --> 00:03:46,289
think about it overnight and, uh...

69
00:03:46,361 --> 00:03:48,295
let me know tomorrow, okay?

70
00:03:49,698 --> 00:03:50,687
Thanks.

71
00:03:50,765 --> 00:03:51,754
Oh! Jeez!

72
00:03:51,833 --> 00:03:53,824
Ma!

73
00:03:53,902 --> 00:03:55,164
I'll be fine.
Thank you very much.

74
00:03:55,237 --> 00:03:56,932
At least let me take
care of your pants.

75
00:03:57,005 --> 00:03:59,565
Mrs. Montanari, you have
enough on your plate.

76
00:03:59,641 --> 00:04:02,610
I'm sorry you had to come
all the way down here for nothing.

77
00:04:02,677 --> 00:04:04,201
I just, I can't think
straight right now.

78
00:04:04,279 --> 00:04:05,268
No, I understand.

79
00:04:05,347 --> 00:04:07,338
You loved him.

80
00:04:07,415 --> 00:04:09,007
He gave me a sandwich.

81
00:04:11,086 --> 00:04:14,886
It was the first time anybody
ever gave me anything.

82
00:04:19,027 --> 00:04:22,019
I'm sorry for your loss, Patty.

83
00:04:45,453 --> 00:04:47,819
You should probably speak up.

84
00:04:49,391 --> 00:04:51,552
I don't think everybody heard you.

85
00:04:51,626 --> 00:04:53,093
You want the ring?

86
00:04:53,161 --> 00:04:54,788
You can have it.

87
00:04:54,863 --> 00:04:56,797
In fact, if you give me a good price,

88
00:04:56,865 --> 00:04:58,264
I'll throw in the pillow, too.

89
00:05:34,502 --> 00:05:36,595
All right, guys, pay attention.

90
00:05:36,671 --> 00:05:38,070
See this ring?

91
00:05:38,139 --> 00:05:40,437
The idea is to keep an eye on the ring.

92
00:05:40,508 --> 00:05:42,476
Here we go.
Put it under the middle cup.

93
00:05:42,544 --> 00:05:45,741
Here we go.
Around and around she goes.

94
00:05:45,814 --> 00:05:47,076
The idea's to watch the ring.

95
00:05:47,148 --> 00:05:50,311
Where is... the ring?

96
00:05:50,385 --> 00:05:51,977
No.

97
00:05:52,053 --> 00:05:53,042
Try again.

98
00:05:53,121 --> 00:05:54,588
It's in your pocket.

99
00:05:56,992 --> 00:05:59,290
Not bad.

100
00:05:59,361 --> 00:06:01,056
You're right.
In my pocket.

101
00:06:01,129 --> 00:06:02,221
You're pretty sharp.

102
00:06:02,297 --> 00:06:03,594
He's not my son for nothing.

103
00:06:08,370 --> 00:06:10,668
I don't have it all.

104
00:06:10,739 --> 00:06:12,070
That's okay.

105
00:06:12,140 --> 00:06:14,199
Hold on to it for now.

106
00:06:14,275 --> 00:06:16,743
<i>Call it a loan.</i>

107
00:06:16,811 --> 00:06:18,836
I didn't ask for a loan.

108
00:06:18,913 --> 00:06:20,244
Well, you might need it.

109
00:06:22,484 --> 00:06:24,008
Thank you, anyway.

110
00:06:24,085 --> 00:06:26,986
<i>Come on, boys.
Let's go find your grandma.</i>

111
00:06:45,340 --> 00:06:46,602
You want to take the boys home?

112
00:06:46,675 --> 00:06:48,472
- I'm going to get a few things.
- All right.

113
00:06:48,543 --> 00:06:49,532
Bye, Mom.
Bye.

114
00:06:49,611 --> 00:06:51,078
I'll see you at home.

115
00:06:51,146 --> 00:06:53,205
Be good for your grandmother.

116
00:06:57,752 --> 00:06:58,980
How are you holding up?

117
00:06:59,054 --> 00:07:01,682
I'm so sorry about Dante.

118
00:07:01,756 --> 00:07:02,745
Yeah.

119
00:07:02,824 --> 00:07:05,054
Well, thank God he's not
in pain anymore, you know?

120
00:07:05,126 --> 00:07:08,027
You're absolutely right.

121
00:07:08,096 --> 00:07:10,394
He was a good man.
He shouldn't be suffering.

122
00:07:11,933 --> 00:07:14,367
You know, Patty, what are we
going to do, you know? Life...

123
00:07:14,436 --> 00:07:16,370
It's a crazy thing.

124
00:07:16,438 --> 00:07:17,632
Okay.

125
00:07:17,706 --> 00:07:20,038
Make it $25.

126
00:07:21,209 --> 00:07:23,439
I'm going to pay you at the end
of the week, okay?

127
00:07:24,746 --> 00:07:28,113
I'm... I'm... I'm sorry.

128
00:07:28,183 --> 00:07:29,616
You know word gets around.

129
00:07:31,519 --> 00:07:33,043
I'm so sorry...
No.

130
00:07:33,121 --> 00:07:34,986
That's... It's okay.

131
00:07:36,891 --> 00:07:38,950
You take care.

132
00:07:55,510 --> 00:07:57,273
Hey!

133
00:07:57,345 --> 00:07:59,438
Put it in sideways.

134
00:08:01,950 --> 00:08:03,042
I knew that.

135
00:08:03,118 --> 00:08:05,678
Hey, I got your cigarettes.

136
00:08:05,754 --> 00:08:07,221
I didn't want to bring
them by the house

137
00:08:07,288 --> 00:08:08,585
what with Dante being sick and all.

138
00:08:08,656 --> 00:08:11,181
Yeah, I quit.

139
00:08:11,259 --> 00:08:12,851
<i>Right. Cancer.</i>

140
00:08:12,927 --> 00:08:14,326
I'm such a dope.

141
00:08:14,395 --> 00:08:17,762
Well, that and I'm, uh, broke.

142
00:08:19,334 --> 00:08:21,302
<i>Hey, come here.
Come on.</i>

143
00:08:21,369 --> 00:08:22,927
- No, what are you doing...
- Come on take this.

144
00:08:23,004 --> 00:08:24,437
- Let me help you out.
- Don't insult me.

145
00:08:24,506 --> 00:08:26,940
- Please, please.
- All right.

146
00:08:27,008 --> 00:08:28,566
Not for nothing.

147
00:08:28,643 --> 00:08:30,941
<i>Come work for me.</i>

148
00:08:31,012 --> 00:08:33,037
Nah. I can't break the law.

149
00:08:33,114 --> 00:08:35,480
Think of it as a public service.

150
00:08:35,550 --> 00:08:36,608
All those taxes.

151
00:08:36,684 --> 00:08:38,675
How are we supposed
to smoke, huh?

152
00:08:44,626 --> 00:08:47,925
Ho, ho, ho!
Merry Christmas!

153
00:08:47,996 --> 00:08:50,692
Hey, Patty, you doing
Jimmy's route?

154
00:08:50,765 --> 00:08:51,823
Hey!

155
00:08:51,900 --> 00:08:53,834
Yeah, I am.

156
00:08:53,902 --> 00:08:55,995
Huh. All right.
All right.

157
00:08:56,070 --> 00:08:57,537
You know what?
Give me one of those.

158
00:08:57,605 --> 00:08:59,766
I thought you quit.
I just changed my mind.

159
00:08:59,841 --> 00:09:01,308
All right.

160
00:09:01,376 --> 00:09:03,173
Oh, thanks, man.

161
00:09:03,244 --> 00:09:05,212
No worries.
Take care.

162
00:09:24,933 --> 00:09:26,867
I always knew I was a genius.

163
00:09:26,935 --> 00:09:28,800
Face like yours,
I'm gonna double my sales.

164
00:09:28,870 --> 00:09:32,033
There you go, babe.
Double?

165
00:09:32,106 --> 00:09:34,131
I'd say that's a conservative estimate.

166
00:09:34,209 --> 00:09:35,836
Frank, we... we were just...

167
00:09:35,910 --> 00:09:37,207
I can see.

168
00:09:38,313 --> 00:09:39,678
Nice hat.

169
00:09:39,747 --> 00:09:40,907
It's very fetching.

170
00:09:40,982 --> 00:09:42,108
Frank, this was a last-minute thing.

171
00:09:42,183 --> 00:09:44,708
I swear to God, I didn't have
a chance to pass it by Bones yet.

172
00:09:44,786 --> 00:09:46,686
You're a big man, Jimmy.

173
00:09:46,754 --> 00:09:48,415
You don't need to tell me
everything you do.

174
00:09:48,489 --> 00:09:49,820
Right.

175
00:09:49,891 --> 00:09:52,860
Okay, then.
I'll, uh...

176
00:09:52,927 --> 00:09:54,827
See you tomorrow.
Right.

177
00:09:57,632 --> 00:09:58,826
What the hell was that about?

178
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:01,391
You took the words
right out of my mouth.

179
00:10:01,469 --> 00:10:04,029
- You told me you don't need money.
- I don't.

180
00:10:04,105 --> 00:10:06,573
Which is why you're wearing
an elf hat, moving stolen goods?

181
00:10:06,641 --> 00:10:09,337
Oh, I don't do this for money,
I do this for fun.

182
00:10:09,410 --> 00:10:12,106
- You should see what I do for money.
- You know you can go to jail for this?

183
00:10:12,180 --> 00:10:13,704
Nobody goes to jail
for selling cigarettes.

184
00:10:13,781 --> 00:10:16,545
Says who, the brain trust
who talked you into doing this?

185
00:10:16,618 --> 00:10:19,143
What's he giving you,
ten cents a pack?

186
00:10:19,220 --> 00:10:21,848
You always get so involved
in other people's personal business?

187
00:10:21,923 --> 00:10:25,017
Ah, the world's got bigger things
in store for you, Mrs. Montanari.

188
00:10:25,093 --> 00:10:27,425
Believe me.
That is very poetic.

189
00:10:27,495 --> 00:10:31,989
<i>But at the moment, I got to make
Christmas happen for my kids.</i>

190
00:10:32,066 --> 00:10:34,899
If you need a job,
come work for me.

191
00:10:34,969 --> 00:10:36,095
At the funeral home?

192
00:10:36,170 --> 00:10:37,933
I won't make you wear funny hats.

193
00:10:38,006 --> 00:10:39,098
No, thanks.

194
00:10:39,173 --> 00:10:40,231
I think I'll pass.

195
00:10:40,308 --> 00:10:42,572
See, a lesser man might feel slighted.

196
00:10:42,644 --> 00:10:46,478
A better man might look for other ways
to make an impression.

197
00:10:52,186 --> 00:10:53,448
Merry Christmas.

198
00:10:57,258 --> 00:10:58,384
Merry Christmas.

199
00:10:58,459 --> 00:11:01,223
And, uh...

200
00:11:01,296 --> 00:11:02,695
good luck with that elf thing.

201
00:11:02,764 --> 00:11:05,198
I don't believe in luck.

202
00:11:06,301 --> 00:11:07,996
Neither do I.

203
00:11:08,169 --> 00:11:10,501
All right, no peeking.

204
00:11:10,571 --> 00:11:13,768
One... two...

205
00:11:13,841 --> 00:11:15,706
three!

206
00:11:17,946 --> 00:11:19,538
Well, don't all shout at once.

207
00:11:19,614 --> 00:11:21,878
But Joey said Santa wasn't coming.

208
00:11:21,950 --> 00:11:23,645
I said "maybe."

209
00:11:23,718 --> 00:11:26,551
Well, Santa always
comes for good boys.

210
00:11:26,621 --> 00:11:27,747
Go ahead.

211
00:11:31,893 --> 00:11:33,622
That's probably him now.

212
00:11:33,695 --> 00:11:35,026
Wise guy.

213
00:11:39,567 --> 00:11:41,432
Mrs. Montanari?
Yeah.

214
00:11:41,502 --> 00:11:44,266
Special Agent Wolford. FBI.

215
00:11:45,273 --> 00:11:46,399
Hi.
Hi.

216
00:11:46,474 --> 00:11:48,101
I was hoping we could talk.

217
00:11:48,176 --> 00:11:50,770
Talk... now... uh...

218
00:11:50,845 --> 00:11:54,110
You know, it's not... it's not really a...

219
00:11:54,182 --> 00:11:55,843
The house isn't... isn't...

220
00:11:55,917 --> 00:11:57,646
I don't mind.

221
00:11:57,719 --> 00:11:59,346
Uh, all right.

222
00:11:59,420 --> 00:12:00,409
<i>Come on in.
Great.</i>

223
00:12:00,488 --> 00:12:03,548
Uh, just right there,
to your right.

224
00:12:11,199 --> 00:12:12,928
Tell me again, huh?

225
00:12:13,001 --> 00:12:14,332
Where is it?
Ah!

226
00:12:14,402 --> 00:12:17,929
I don't know!

227
00:12:18,006 --> 00:12:19,633
I don't know, please.

228
00:12:19,707 --> 00:12:21,572
The guards,
they took me in at the border.

229
00:12:21,642 --> 00:12:22,870
They asked me questions.

230
00:12:22,944 --> 00:12:24,878
When I came out, I drove away.

231
00:12:24,946 --> 00:12:26,436
I pulled the car over straightaway.

232
00:12:26,514 --> 00:12:29,210
There was no suitcase.

233
00:12:29,283 --> 00:12:31,410
I swear on my kid's eyes, Carmine!

234
00:12:31,486 --> 00:12:33,454
I swear!
On his eyes?

235
00:12:33,521 --> 00:12:35,045
You swear, do you?
I swear!

236
00:12:35,123 --> 00:12:37,489
Maybe I should open
your head up and check!

237
00:12:39,193 --> 00:12:41,593
That's enough for now.

238
00:12:41,662 --> 00:12:43,027
<i>Carmine...</i>

239
00:12:43,097 --> 00:12:44,359
come here.

240
00:12:44,432 --> 00:12:46,366
Give me that.
Okay.

241
00:12:46,434 --> 00:12:48,664
You lying sack of...

242
00:12:48,736 --> 00:12:51,432
Hey.
These are my boys.

243
00:12:51,506 --> 00:12:53,098
Thanks, Ma.

244
00:12:54,509 --> 00:12:56,977
So, uh...

245
00:12:57,045 --> 00:12:59,104
you know, shouldn't you
be out celebrating?

246
00:12:59,180 --> 00:13:00,340
Families?

247
00:13:00,415 --> 00:13:03,873
Just tying up a few
loose ends, really.

248
00:13:05,253 --> 00:13:06,584
Okay.

249
00:13:06,654 --> 00:13:09,316
Rich, where's the money?

250
00:13:09,390 --> 00:13:10,755
Frankie, I don't have it.

251
00:13:14,395 --> 00:13:16,363
What am I supposed
to tell Palmeri?

252
00:13:16,431 --> 00:13:17,420
That you lost it?

253
00:13:17,498 --> 00:13:19,227
- I don't have it.
- I got a problem with that.

254
00:13:19,300 --> 00:13:21,894
That's $500,000.

255
00:13:21,969 --> 00:13:23,960
You want me to believe that
the border patrol got lucky,

256
00:13:24,038 --> 00:13:25,027
is that what it is?

257
00:13:25,106 --> 00:13:27,597
It's either that or somebody
tipped them off.

258
00:13:27,675 --> 00:13:29,233
Who tipped them off, Richie?

259
00:13:29,310 --> 00:13:30,971
Who tipped them off?
I didn't, Frank.

260
00:13:31,045 --> 00:13:34,071
And if I find out it was you,

261
00:13:34,148 --> 00:13:36,742
I'm going to drill
a hole in your brain,

262
00:13:36,818 --> 00:13:38,843
then I'm going to drill
a hole in your heart,

263
00:13:38,920 --> 00:13:41,480
then drill a hole
in each one of your eyes.

264
00:13:41,556 --> 00:13:43,183
Now, if you'll excuse me,

265
00:13:43,257 --> 00:13:46,749
I got to go open presents
with my family.

266
00:13:46,828 --> 00:13:50,161
Bones, take him in the car out back.

267
00:13:50,231 --> 00:13:51,698
What about the restaurant, Frank?

268
00:13:54,502 --> 00:13:56,834
The restaurant?

269
00:13:56,904 --> 00:13:59,338
Well, you just gave it to me, right?

270
00:14:01,209 --> 00:14:02,642
Yeah.
What do you say?

271
00:14:02,710 --> 00:14:04,735
Yeah, Merry Christmas, Frank.

272
00:14:04,812 --> 00:14:06,507
Merry Christmas, Richie.

273
00:14:06,581 --> 00:14:08,071
Yeah.
Let's go.

274
00:14:08,149 --> 00:14:10,913
So, um, you know Jimmy Limo?

275
00:14:10,985 --> 00:14:12,145
Yeah.

276
00:14:12,220 --> 00:14:15,212
'Cause some people are saying
you guys might be working together.

277
00:14:15,289 --> 00:14:16,278
Well, that's weird.

278
00:14:16,357 --> 00:14:18,450
Maybe he didn't explain
some things to you, but, uh...

279
00:14:20,294 --> 00:14:22,956
People who sell cigarettes
are required to pay taxes,

280
00:14:23,030 --> 00:14:25,726
and not paying those taxes
is a federal offense

281
00:14:25,800 --> 00:14:27,893
for which you can be put into prison.

282
00:14:27,969 --> 00:14:29,664
Is that right?

283
00:14:29,737 --> 00:14:30,726
Yeah, that's right.

284
00:14:30,805 --> 00:14:33,330
Well, it's a good thing
I'm not working for him then, huh?

285
00:14:33,407 --> 00:14:35,841
Okay.
All right.

286
00:14:35,910 --> 00:14:38,276
Excellent.

287
00:14:40,381 --> 00:14:42,110
May I?
Yeah.

288
00:14:43,584 --> 00:14:45,313
Oh, jeez...
Oh, no, it's all right.

289
00:14:45,386 --> 00:14:46,648
I'm sorry.
No, it's all right.

290
00:14:46,721 --> 00:14:47,745
It's all right.
Oh, God.

291
00:14:47,822 --> 00:14:48,982
I didn't really like it anyway.

292
00:14:49,056 --> 00:14:50,887
Hey, listen.

293
00:14:50,958 --> 00:14:52,983
You need to be careful, okay?

294
00:14:53,060 --> 00:14:54,687
He's part of the Gambino family.

295
00:14:54,762 --> 00:14:56,286
He works under Salvatore Palmeri.

296
00:14:58,166 --> 00:15:00,031
He's in the Mob?

297
00:15:00,101 --> 00:15:01,090
Yeah.

298
00:15:08,209 --> 00:15:09,403
Okay...

299
00:15:11,212 --> 00:15:13,043
Right here.

300
00:15:13,114 --> 00:15:14,877
Take 'em out,
you put 'em right here.

301
00:15:14,949 --> 00:15:17,042
All right, here we go.

302
00:15:17,118 --> 00:15:18,107
Ooh!

303
00:15:18,186 --> 00:15:19,483
Thank you.
I'll get them, lady.

304
00:15:19,554 --> 00:15:22,990
I'm going to help you, all right?
Let me help you.

305
00:15:24,825 --> 00:15:27,089
Frank, we should have
done it right there,

306
00:15:27,161 --> 00:15:29,186
before it comes back
and bites us in the ass.

307
00:15:29,263 --> 00:15:31,254
We'll give it some time,
see how it plays out.

308
00:15:31,332 --> 00:15:33,357
Okay, we'll give it some time.

309
00:15:35,603 --> 00:15:36,934
What the hell is that?

310
00:15:38,339 --> 00:15:40,432
Ho!

311
00:15:40,508 --> 00:15:43,443
Ho! What are you doing?
Put those back.

312
00:15:43,511 --> 00:15:45,001
Hey, put those back.

313
00:15:45,079 --> 00:15:46,410
Put those back.
What the hell's this?

314
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:48,038
- Don't listen to him. Keep going.
- Put 'em back.

315
00:15:48,115 --> 00:15:49,412
- You keep going.
- Who are you?

316
00:15:49,483 --> 00:15:51,542
- Who am I? Who are you?
- Who am I? What are you...

317
00:15:51,619 --> 00:15:52,984
These belong to Mr. Russo.

318
00:15:53,054 --> 00:15:55,215
If he would like them moved,
he can come out here

319
00:15:55,289 --> 00:15:56,847
- and do it himself.
- Are you out of your mind?

320
00:15:56,924 --> 00:15:58,448
- Put that...
- Hey, it's okay. It's okay.

321
00:15:58,526 --> 00:16:00,756
It's okay, just move this stuff
inside already, will you?

322
00:16:00,828 --> 00:16:02,887
- Come on, let's get it off the sidewalk.
- All right, go.

323
00:16:02,964 --> 00:16:05,125
Go. Move it. You heard him,
move it inside. Get in there.

324
00:16:05,199 --> 00:16:06,757
You know what you are?

325
00:16:06,834 --> 00:16:09,428
A bully. And a hypocrite.

326
00:16:09,503 --> 00:16:11,061
<i>Calling the FBI to
keep me from selling</i>

327
00:16:11,138 --> 00:16:13,436
a few cigarettes when
you do worse every day.

328
00:16:13,507 --> 00:16:15,236
- You don't know what I do.
- Oh, no?

329
00:16:15,309 --> 00:16:17,209
Tell me I'm wrong.

330
00:16:17,278 --> 00:16:19,769
Tell me I'm wrong,
and I'll pack it all up and go home.

331
00:16:19,847 --> 00:16:22,407
Jimmy Limo has been working
this neighborhood for 20 years.

332
00:16:22,483 --> 00:16:25,008
No FBI agent ever come
to his house on Christmas Eve.

333
00:16:25,086 --> 00:16:27,145
No, I was helping you
make smart choices,

334
00:16:27,221 --> 00:16:29,621
but since you obviously aren't
capable of listening to reason,

335
00:16:29,690 --> 00:16:30,987
maybe we need
to do something else.

336
00:16:31,058 --> 00:16:32,650
You know what?
I don't respond to threats.

337
00:16:32,727 --> 00:16:33,887
That wasn't a threat.

338
00:16:33,961 --> 00:16:37,192
Trust me, if I threatened you,
you'd know.

339
00:16:37,265 --> 00:16:39,256
You know what my mother says?

340
00:16:39,333 --> 00:16:41,801
Never trust a man
who says to "trust me."

341
00:16:43,137 --> 00:16:43,933
<i>Come with me.</i>

342
00:16:44,005 --> 00:16:46,439
<i>- No.
- Come on. Come take a walk.</i>

343
00:16:46,507 --> 00:16:47,804
I'm not going anywhere with you.

344
00:16:47,875 --> 00:16:50,435
Whoa! What the hell are you doing?

345
00:16:50,511 --> 00:16:51,944
<i>Carmine, take care
of these guys, will you?</i>

346
00:16:52,013 --> 00:16:55,676
Frank, I got it.
Hey, put me down right now!

347
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:57,513
Afternoon, Mr. Russo.

348
00:16:57,585 --> 00:17:00,645
- Hey, Merry Christmas, Tom.
- Oh, hi, Tom!

349
00:17:00,721 --> 00:17:03,212
- And to you, too.
- You know Patty?

350
00:17:03,291 --> 00:17:04,781
Put me down!

351
00:17:04,859 --> 00:17:07,054
And you're embarrassing me.

352
00:17:07,128 --> 00:17:08,857
Don't you ever do that again.

353
00:17:08,929 --> 00:17:10,863
Take a look at this.

354
00:17:11,899 --> 00:17:12,923
It's yours.

355
00:17:13,000 --> 00:17:14,627
I want you to run it however you like.

356
00:17:14,702 --> 00:17:17,432
All you have to do is pay me rent,
you pocket the profits.

357
00:17:17,505 --> 00:17:18,699
Are you crazy?

358
00:17:18,773 --> 00:17:20,934
You need a job,
I just acquired a piece of property.

359
00:17:21,008 --> 00:17:21,997
You don't even know me.

360
00:17:22,076 --> 00:17:23,600
But everybody deserves a chance.

361
00:17:23,678 --> 00:17:26,772
I wouldn't work for you if you were
the last person on the planet.

362
00:17:26,847 --> 00:17:27,836
I don't think that's true.

363
00:17:27,915 --> 00:17:31,851
I think you do whatever it takes
to put food on the table.

364
00:17:31,919 --> 00:17:35,685
And you're too smart to walk away
from the best opportunity you ever seen.

365
00:17:37,058 --> 00:17:38,889
Am I right?

366
00:17:38,959 --> 00:17:40,790
<i>In the end, he won.</i>

367
00:17:40,861 --> 00:17:43,796
<i>The same way he wins every time.</i>

368
00:17:43,864 --> 00:17:45,388
<i>Not with threats...</i>

369
00:17:45,466 --> 00:17:46,524
No strings?

370
00:17:46,600 --> 00:17:47,965
On my life.

371
00:17:48,035 --> 00:17:49,229
<i>... with promises.</i>

372
00:17:49,303 --> 00:17:50,770
Want to take a look, huh?

373
00:17:50,838 --> 00:17:53,102
- Check it out?
- Don't you touch me.

374
00:17:58,846 --> 00:18:02,213
Regrettably, the restaurant has run
into some financial difficulties.

375
00:18:02,283 --> 00:18:04,751
Originally, I was going to close, but, uh,

376
00:18:04,819 --> 00:18:06,946
after meeting Mrs. Montanari,

377
00:18:07,021 --> 00:18:09,751
I became convinced
that a person with her visión...

378
00:18:09,824 --> 00:18:11,018
Excuse me, Dad.

379
00:18:11,092 --> 00:18:12,150
Not right now.

380
00:18:12,226 --> 00:18:13,989
Dad, I need to talk to you.

381
00:18:15,930 --> 00:18:17,158
We got heat.

382
00:18:17,231 --> 00:18:19,392
I think the wife filed
a missing persons report.

383
00:18:19,467 --> 00:18:21,298
You should come outside, okay?

384
00:18:21,369 --> 00:18:22,927
- Okay. Good, son.
- No problem.

385
00:18:23,003 --> 00:18:26,666
Uh, Mrs. Montanari,
would you care to finish?

386
00:18:29,577 --> 00:18:31,636
Uh... okay.

387
00:18:31,712 --> 00:18:36,149
Well, first of all,
you can call me Patty. Uh,

388
00:18:36,217 --> 00:18:38,185
and I think that once we all
get to know each other,

389
00:18:38,252 --> 00:18:40,379
we're going to have a really great...

390
00:18:40,454 --> 00:18:42,285
time.

391
00:18:42,356 --> 00:18:45,223
All right.

392
00:18:47,194 --> 00:18:49,628
Well, I'm glad somebody
thinks that's funny.

393
00:18:49,697 --> 00:18:52,257
Look, honey, I don't know
who you screwed to get this job,

394
00:18:52,333 --> 00:18:54,358
but I'm telling you right now,
it's no prize.

395
00:18:54,435 --> 00:18:56,995
And if the last guy
couldn't make it work,

396
00:18:57,071 --> 00:18:59,631
well, then, uh...
you don't stand a chance.

397
00:18:59,707 --> 00:19:03,165
Meanwhile,
you got a way to make rent?

398
00:19:05,746 --> 00:19:09,204
How I pay my rent...
is none of your business.

399
00:19:09,283 --> 00:19:12,184
My mistake.
The way we were talking,

400
00:19:12,253 --> 00:19:15,984
I thought that maybe
we could be friends.

401
00:19:19,026 --> 00:19:21,824
Well, my friends...

402
00:19:21,896 --> 00:19:24,160
usually call me June.

403
00:19:24,231 --> 00:19:25,459
Okay, here's the thing.

404
00:19:25,533 --> 00:19:27,501
As long as you work for these goombahs,
you're doomed.

405
00:19:27,568 --> 00:19:29,536
I mean, they're going
to show up one day with,

406
00:19:29,603 --> 00:19:30,934
you know, a truckload of hijacked cows,

407
00:19:31,005 --> 00:19:32,905
and, all of a sudden,
you're running a steak house.

408
00:19:32,973 --> 00:19:34,463
The next day, shrimp.

409
00:19:34,542 --> 00:19:37,170
Or some other thing you never
heard of and no one can eat.

410
00:19:37,244 --> 00:19:38,836
Maybe I should make it a bar.

411
00:19:38,913 --> 00:19:40,505
There are 15 bars on this street.

412
00:19:40,581 --> 00:19:42,173
None of them have ever broken even.

413
00:19:42,249 --> 00:19:44,615
You have a very negative attitude,
do you know that?

414
00:19:44,685 --> 00:19:45,743
Well, I'm just saying that...

415
00:19:45,820 --> 00:19:50,689
that these psychos are the only reason
this place ever stays open.

416
00:19:50,758 --> 00:19:52,020
Well...

417
00:19:52,092 --> 00:19:56,256
then I will just have to make it
successful enough to run on its own.

418
00:19:58,799 --> 00:20:00,562
<i>Salud.</i>

419
00:20:02,002 --> 00:20:03,799
You know, the place is an arm pit.

420
00:20:03,871 --> 00:20:06,271
It never made nobody a nickel.

421
00:20:06,340 --> 00:20:07,773
I say we burn it down.

422
00:20:07,842 --> 00:20:10,310
We give the insurance money
to Palmeri, and that's it.

423
00:20:10,377 --> 00:20:12,470
Yeah, well, maybe it needs
a fresh pair of eyes.

424
00:20:12,546 --> 00:20:15,037
<i>Come on, Frank, we owe the guy
half a million bucks.</i>

425
00:20:15,115 --> 00:20:17,345
This may not be the best time
to launch a, what,

426
00:20:17,418 --> 00:20:18,908
culinary experiment, you know?

427
00:20:18,986 --> 00:20:20,283
You're retarded. Listen, Frank.

428
00:20:20,354 --> 00:20:23,187
I think maybe you're thinking
with the wrong part of your body.

429
00:20:23,257 --> 00:20:24,588
Ho! With all due respect, boss.

430
00:20:24,658 --> 00:20:26,922
I'm saying, what do you want
a broad in there for?

431
00:20:26,994 --> 00:20:28,825
Her? I can think of a few reasons.

432
00:20:28,896 --> 00:20:30,955
Hey, Jimmy, I'm serious.

433
00:20:31,031 --> 00:20:33,499
I mean, don't we all get
enough trouble at home?

434
00:20:33,567 --> 00:20:34,932
That's true.

435
00:20:35,002 --> 00:20:36,435
- Point taken.
- Hey, no women in here.

436
00:20:36,504 --> 00:20:37,869
Whoa!

437
00:20:37,938 --> 00:20:39,872
Oh, no, no, no, no, no, no, no.

438
00:20:39,940 --> 00:20:41,407
I'm so glad I found you.

439
00:20:41,475 --> 00:20:42,840
I have to show you this.

440
00:20:42,910 --> 00:20:45,435
- Are you kidding?
- Oh, here we go.

441
00:20:45,513 --> 00:20:47,071
They do a show in the Village.

442
00:20:47,147 --> 00:20:48,842
It's sold out for months.

443
00:20:48,916 --> 00:20:50,884
No way that's a guy.

444
00:20:50,951 --> 00:20:54,819
- Why would you do that to yourself?
- I was thinking we could have one like it.

445
00:20:54,889 --> 00:20:57,289
Frank,
we ain't running no gay bar.

446
00:20:57,358 --> 00:20:59,792
The place in the Village
clears 10 grand a night.

447
00:20:59,860 --> 00:21:01,054
Whoa.

448
00:21:01,128 --> 00:21:04,120
Why don't we talk about this
over dinner?

449
00:21:06,634 --> 00:21:09,102
Oh, no. Oh, no. I got to go.

450
00:21:09,169 --> 00:21:11,160
<i>Come on, Nino.
That's your turn.</i>

451
00:21:11,238 --> 00:21:13,729
Yeah, two.

452
00:21:13,807 --> 00:21:16,298
I'm sorry.

453
00:21:16,377 --> 00:21:18,607
I'm so sorry. Hi.

454
00:21:18,679 --> 00:21:20,772
I'm so sorry, Sister Carolina.

455
00:21:20,848 --> 00:21:23,180
Mrs. Montanari,
this isn't a baby-sitting service.

456
00:21:23,250 --> 00:21:24,342
I know, I know.

457
00:21:24,418 --> 00:21:25,851
It won't happen again, I promise.

458
00:21:25,920 --> 00:21:27,717
Hi, boys.

459
00:21:27,788 --> 00:21:30,723
So... how was everybody's day?

460
00:21:32,459 --> 00:21:34,723
Okay, we'll talk about it at home.

461
00:21:34,795 --> 00:21:36,695
I'm sorry.

462
00:21:36,764 --> 00:21:38,732
It's a big job, you know?

463
00:21:38,799 --> 00:21:40,266
And I'm still getting used to it.

464
00:21:40,334 --> 00:21:42,199
Then why'd they give it to you?

465
00:21:42,269 --> 00:21:43,964
Don't hold back.

466
00:21:44,038 --> 00:21:46,506
I'm serious. You're a mother.

467
00:21:46,574 --> 00:21:48,769
How'd you end up
running a nightclub?

468
00:21:48,842 --> 00:21:49,968
Well, maybe I have talent.

469
00:21:50,044 --> 00:21:52,774
You make good sandwiches.

470
00:21:52,846 --> 00:21:54,245
All right, so we have two bars...

471
00:21:54,315 --> 00:21:55,680
one here and one in the back

472
00:21:55,749 --> 00:21:57,512
so nobody ever has to wait for drinks.

473
00:21:57,585 --> 00:21:59,917
The dance floor is going
to be Brazilian mahogany.

474
00:21:59,987 --> 00:22:02,251
It costs more, but it doesn't scratch.

475
00:22:02,323 --> 00:22:04,757
Yeah, and what's, uh...
What's that back there?

476
00:22:04,825 --> 00:22:06,417
Oh, that's a stage.

477
00:22:06,493 --> 00:22:09,257
Get 'em thirsty
and keep 'em entertained.

478
00:22:09,330 --> 00:22:13,164
Well, I should put you in charge
of my lots in Florida.

479
00:22:18,572 --> 00:22:20,096
What do you think?

480
00:22:20,174 --> 00:22:21,266
<i>Come on.</i>

481
00:22:21,342 --> 00:22:23,207
- What?
- Come on. Let's dance.

482
00:22:23,277 --> 00:22:24,437
No, I'm not dancing with you.

483
00:22:24,511 --> 00:22:26,274
- Why not?
- Because, I...

484
00:22:26,347 --> 00:22:28,110
Well, I don't know...
I don't know how to dance.

485
00:22:28,182 --> 00:22:29,809
Well, you don't know
how to run a nightclub, either.

486
00:22:29,883 --> 00:22:30,907
<i>Come on.</i>

487
00:22:30,985 --> 00:22:32,919
What about your wife?

488
00:22:32,987 --> 00:22:35,182
She doesn't like to dance.

489
00:22:35,255 --> 00:22:37,018
Please?

490
00:22:37,091 --> 00:22:39,082
All right.

491
00:22:40,227 --> 00:22:43,492
<i>I just don't know how</i>

492
00:22:43,564 --> 00:22:46,556
<i>Oh, girl</i>

493
00:22:47,568 --> 00:22:49,399
<i>How I depend on you...</i>

494
00:22:49,470 --> 00:22:51,301
- You all right?
- Yeah.

495
00:22:51,372 --> 00:22:52,634
There you go.

496
00:22:52,706 --> 00:22:54,936
<i>To give me love when I need it</i>

497
00:22:55,009 --> 00:22:57,842
<i>Right on time
you would always be...</i>

498
00:22:57,911 --> 00:22:59,845
I thought you didn't know how to dance.

499
00:22:59,913 --> 00:23:01,904
I... I don't.

500
00:23:05,352 --> 00:23:06,819
Whole new life.

501
00:23:10,691 --> 00:23:12,181
Excuse me for interrupting.

502
00:23:15,596 --> 00:23:17,223
<i>Come on in, Tom.</i>

503
00:23:17,297 --> 00:23:19,697
Mr. Russo,

504
00:23:19,767 --> 00:23:22,361
I just want to say I'm pleased

505
00:23:22,436 --> 00:23:24,427
that this property
has come into your hands,

506
00:23:24,505 --> 00:23:26,598
and I know that,
under your guidance,

507
00:23:26,674 --> 00:23:28,938
we can expect nothing but greatness.

508
00:23:29,009 --> 00:23:30,943
Wow.
This is for you.

509
00:23:31,011 --> 00:23:32,273
Thanks, Tom.

510
00:23:32,346 --> 00:23:33,608
Nothing but greatness.

511
00:23:33,681 --> 00:23:35,615
Just, uh, one other thing.

