that they didn't want,

767
00:38:01,948 --> 00:38:05,315
and I very much respect
your decision.

768
00:38:06,686 --> 00:38:07,983
I didn't make a decision.

769
00:38:11,057 --> 00:38:13,491
I'll do it once,
see how it feels.

770
00:38:13,560 --> 00:38:16,154
Then I'll make my decision.

771
00:38:16,229 --> 00:38:18,060
Good.

772
00:38:32,278 --> 00:38:33,302
What was that?

773
00:38:33,379 --> 00:38:34,539
What was what?

774
00:38:34,614 --> 00:38:35,979
That thing you
were doing with him.

775
00:38:36,049 --> 00:38:37,414
I don't know what
you're talking about.

776
00:38:37,483 --> 00:38:39,508
I'm talking about the way
you were acting with Sal...

777
00:38:39,586 --> 00:38:40,610
like it was a private
conversation.

778
00:38:40,687 --> 00:38:42,177
We were making
a business arrangement.

779
00:38:42,255 --> 00:38:43,654
What, you think
you can play him?

780
00:38:43,723 --> 00:38:45,884
You can't play him, Patty.
He's playing you.

781
00:38:45,959 --> 00:38:47,119
You're acting like a baby.

782
00:38:47,193 --> 00:38:48,956
Do you know what
you have to do?

783
00:38:49,028 --> 00:38:50,586
You know what
he asked you to do?

784
00:38:50,663 --> 00:38:53,257
Yes, he asked me to drive to Canada
and pick up some money.

785
00:38:53,333 --> 00:38:54,891
Yeah, these guys are
not like us, Patty.

786
00:38:54,968 --> 00:38:56,902
They're Sicilian.
They don't work with women.

787
00:38:56,970 --> 00:38:58,096
You try and take their money,

788
00:38:58,171 --> 00:38:59,638
you're gonna end up
in the drink.

789
00:38:59,706 --> 00:39:02,266
And if not, you still got
to make it past the border.

790
00:39:02,342 --> 00:39:03,900
So it's okay that I work for you?

791
00:39:03,977 --> 00:39:05,774
Look, Patty, the last guy
that went up there,

792
00:39:05,845 --> 00:39:09,337
he lost $500,000,
now he's dead.

793
00:39:11,551 --> 00:39:12,950
You want to go up there?

794
00:39:13,019 --> 00:39:14,646
Why didn't you say anything?

795
00:39:14,721 --> 00:39:16,416
I was looking right at you!

796
00:39:16,489 --> 00:39:18,650
I said to you,
"Frank, what do you think?"

797
00:39:18,725 --> 00:39:20,818
'Cause it's not my place
to say no for you.

798
00:39:20,893 --> 00:39:22,451
Why would I say no?

799
00:39:22,528 --> 00:39:24,553
The guy promised
to take care of my kids

800
00:39:24,631 --> 00:39:27,566
for the rest of their lives.

801
00:39:31,304 --> 00:39:32,396
Then take this.

802
00:39:34,107 --> 00:39:35,199
Get that out of here.

803
00:39:35,274 --> 00:39:36,366
No... if you're gonna go,

804
00:39:36,442 --> 00:39:39,275
take it; if not, don't go.

805
00:39:50,857 --> 00:39:53,087
<i>The easy way to explain things</i>

806
00:39:53,159 --> 00:39:54,456
<i>is that my mother was bullied,</i>

807
00:39:54,527 --> 00:39:57,087
<i>or tricked, or even
backed into a corner.</i>

808
00:39:57,163 --> 00:39:59,097
<i>But it wouldn't be true.</i>

809
00:39:59,165 --> 00:40:03,067
<i>She walked in of her own free
will with her eyes wide open.</i>

810
00:40:03,136 --> 00:40:05,934
<i>And she'd be the first to say it.</i>

811
00:40:20,086 --> 00:40:21,917
How long are you going?

812
00:40:23,022 --> 00:40:24,956
Uh, just a few days.

813
00:40:25,024 --> 00:40:27,254
I'll be back before you know it.

814
00:40:27,326 --> 00:40:30,659
If I were you,
I'd take the bullets.

815
00:40:55,288 --> 00:40:57,256
Right through here.

816
00:40:57,323 --> 00:40:59,883
Watch your step.

817
00:41:11,437 --> 00:41:13,064
<i>Don't be afraid.
Come on in.</i>

818
00:41:13,139 --> 00:41:14,231
Straight ahead.

819
00:41:20,880 --> 00:41:22,814
Around the corner here.

820
00:41:29,155 --> 00:41:30,918
Straight ahead.

821
00:41:30,990 --> 00:41:32,252
Around the corner.

822
00:41:33,259 --> 00:41:34,487
Here, you can wait right here.

823
00:41:45,638 --> 00:41:47,230
Seven out.

824
00:41:59,519 --> 00:42:00,850
Watch your step.

825
00:42:13,466 --> 00:42:14,899
...Patty...

826
00:42:27,346 --> 00:42:30,440
Okay, the part,
I understood.

827
00:42:30,516 --> 00:42:31,915
It's not very nice.

828
00:42:31,984 --> 00:42:33,781
You kiss your mother
with that mouth?

829
00:42:33,853 --> 00:42:36,845
I also think you said
something about $400,000

830
00:42:36,923 --> 00:42:39,153
instead of $500,000.

831
00:42:39,225 --> 00:42:41,887
You give me the $500,000

832
00:42:41,961 --> 00:42:44,361
and I will let you keep
your family jewels.

833
00:42:59,712 --> 00:43:02,180
<i>What you want</i>

834
00:43:02,248 --> 00:43:04,375
<i>Baby, I got</i>

835
00:43:04,450 --> 00:43:05,474
<i>What you need</i>

836
00:43:05,551 --> 00:43:06,916
<i>You know I got it</i>

837
00:43:06,986 --> 00:43:09,181
<i>All I'm asking...</i>

838
00:43:09,255 --> 00:43:10,449
Somebody's having fun.

839
00:43:10,523 --> 00:43:13,117
Somebody had
a very nice vacation.

840
00:43:14,327 --> 00:43:15,692
Turn off the music, ma'am.

841
00:43:15,761 --> 00:43:18,161
Let me see some I.D.

842
00:43:18,231 --> 00:43:19,528
Sure.

843
00:43:24,804 --> 00:43:26,237
Here you go.

844
00:43:27,773 --> 00:43:30,367
<i>Could you pop the trunk?</i>

845
00:43:30,443 --> 00:43:32,206
Uh, can we skip it?

846
00:43:32,278 --> 00:43:34,508
I did a lot of shopping,
and I promised the boys

847
00:43:34,580 --> 00:43:36,980
that I'd be home in time
to make pancakes.

848
00:43:37,049 --> 00:43:39,916
Pop the trunk, please.

849
00:43:39,986 --> 00:43:42,454
Yeah.

850
00:44:27,033 --> 00:44:29,001
You did good.

851
00:44:29,068 --> 00:44:31,161
Well, I told you.

852
00:44:31,237 --> 00:44:33,762
The exchange rate
is very favorable.

853
00:44:33,839 --> 00:44:35,431
Have a nice day.

854
00:44:35,508 --> 00:44:36,497
You, too.

855
00:44:48,254 --> 00:44:50,154
<i>My mother makes no excuses</i>

856
00:44:50,222 --> 00:44:51,814
<i>for the choices she made.</i>

857
00:44:51,891 --> 00:44:53,654
<i>But she would also say,</i>

858
00:44:53,726 --> 00:44:55,990
<i>don't be too quick to assume
you wouldn't make them, too.</i>

859
00:45:06,172 --> 00:45:07,503
What are you doing?

860
00:45:07,573 --> 00:45:09,097
<i>What are you doing?</i>

861
00:45:09,175 --> 00:45:10,665
Is that real?

862
00:45:10,743 --> 00:45:13,211
Why aren't you in school?

863
00:45:13,279 --> 00:45:14,746
Grandma went shopping.

864
00:45:14,814 --> 00:45:15,838
She went shopping?

865
00:45:15,915 --> 00:45:17,507
She said there was a sale.

866
00:45:17,583 --> 00:45:19,517
She needed
to get there early.

867
00:45:19,585 --> 00:45:21,416
Okay, the two of you,
you just wait right there.

868
00:45:21,487 --> 00:45:23,614
I'm going to go change
and I'm taking you to school.

869
00:45:23,689 --> 00:45:25,020
Okay.

870
00:45:25,091 --> 00:45:27,082
Hey!

871
00:45:28,260 --> 00:45:29,693
- Whoa.
- Whoa.

872
00:45:29,762 --> 00:45:31,161
Are those for us?

873
00:45:31,230 --> 00:45:32,356
I don't know.

874
00:45:32,431 --> 00:45:33,762
Is your name Nino?

875
00:45:35,735 --> 00:45:37,999
Yeah, go ahead.

876
00:45:38,070 --> 00:45:39,560
<i>Come on, I'll take you.</i>

877
00:45:39,638 --> 00:45:41,299
100 bucks says you can't
beat me to school.

878
00:45:41,374 --> 00:45:42,932
What are you going
to do with $100?

879
00:45:44,210 --> 00:45:45,199
Out of my way.

880
00:45:45,277 --> 00:45:48,872
Coming through, coming through.

881
00:45:51,917 --> 00:45:54,317
What'd you do that for?

882
00:45:54,387 --> 00:45:55,979
I don't know.

883
00:45:56,055 --> 00:45:57,181
Maybe to, uh,

884
00:45:57,256 --> 00:45:59,520
correct a misimpression
I might have left

885
00:45:59,592 --> 00:46:00,923
last time we were together.

886
00:46:00,993 --> 00:46:03,553
Which would be?

887
00:46:03,629 --> 00:46:05,256
That I was a small-minded,

888
00:46:05,331 --> 00:46:08,391
old-fashioned,
jealous sort of person

889
00:46:08,467 --> 00:46:10,833
who could underestimate
the capabilities

890
00:46:10,903 --> 00:46:12,837
of the woman he loves.

891
00:46:14,707 --> 00:46:16,402
I don't think she came to that conclusion.

892
00:46:16,475 --> 00:46:18,773
She didn't?

893
00:46:18,844 --> 00:46:20,334
No.

894
00:46:21,414 --> 00:46:24,577
I think she was just really happy
you were here when she got home.

895
00:46:28,287 --> 00:46:30,414
<i>Come on, get on.
Get on!</i>

896
00:46:30,489 --> 00:46:32,787
- We got to beat these kids to school.
- All right, all right.

897
00:46:33,926 --> 00:46:35,791
That's it, that's it.
Watch your feet.

898
00:46:37,029 --> 00:46:39,020
We're coming, fellas!

899
00:47:19,538 --> 00:47:20,562
<i>Six years later,</i>

900
00:47:20,639 --> 00:47:22,300
<i>and my mother was
as tight with the Mob</i>

901
00:47:22,374 --> 00:47:23,898
<i>as if she were a made guy.</i>

902
00:47:23,976 --> 00:47:25,136
<i>She was involved
in loan-sharking</i>

903
00:47:25,211 --> 00:47:27,145
<i>and ran crap games
all over Brooklyn.</i>

904
00:47:27,213 --> 00:47:30,182
<i>Between the nightclub
and her collections in Canada,</i>

905
00:47:30,249 --> 00:47:31,682
<i>she earned enough money
to move us</i>

906
00:47:31,750 --> 00:47:33,479
<i>from an apartment
on Flatbush Avenue</i>

907
00:47:33,552 --> 00:47:35,179
<i>to a townhouse
in Prospect Park,</i>

908
00:47:35,254 --> 00:47:38,690
<i>and helped Frank pay off the
half mil he owed Sal Palmeri.</i>

909
00:47:38,757 --> 00:47:40,850
<i>\Where's that Parmesan?</i>

910
00:47:40,926 --> 00:47:43,019
<i>But it wasn't for power or money.</i>

911
00:47:43,095 --> 00:47:45,086
<i>The reason she did it was family...</i>

912
00:47:48,701 --> 00:47:50,328
<i>You've done me wrong</i>

913
00:47:50,402 --> 00:47:52,461
<i>... a bigger, more devoted
family than she had ever known.</i>

914
00:47:52,538 --> 00:47:54,506
<i>- You took a sip
- Just a sip</i>

915
00:47:54,573 --> 00:47:57,007
<i>From the Devil's cup</i>

916
00:47:57,076 --> 00:47:58,771
<i>These guys showed up
for everything...</i>

917
00:47:58,844 --> 00:48:00,709
<i>Uncle Al, Uncle Tito,</i>

918
00:48:00,779 --> 00:48:02,644
<i>Uncle Jimmy, Uncle Bones,</i>

919
00:48:02,715 --> 00:48:04,273
<i>Uncle Carmine.</i>

920
00:48:04,350 --> 00:48:07,342
<i>Just who do you think you are</i>

921
00:48:08,754 --> 00:48:11,188
<i>Stop acting like
some kind of star</i>

922
00:48:11,257 --> 00:48:12,519
Not so fast.

923
00:48:12,591 --> 00:48:14,525
This is for college.

924
00:48:14,593 --> 00:48:16,561
Home in an hour.

925
00:48:16,629 --> 00:48:19,564
<i>And that was just
the immediate family.</i>

926
00:48:19,632 --> 00:48:22,567
<i>There was also Eddie and Mikey,
Jackie and Vic.</i>

927
00:48:22,635 --> 00:48:24,159
<i>Even the cops.</i>

928
00:48:24,236 --> 00:48:26,830
<i>So many guys on the take it
made you wonder who wasn't.</i>

929
00:48:26,906 --> 00:48:28,897
<i>Breaking the law was just
the price they all paid</i>

930
00:48:28,974 --> 00:48:30,908
<i>to be part of things.</i>

931
00:48:30,976 --> 00:48:32,409
Hey, Patty...

932
00:48:32,478 --> 00:48:34,412
you, uh, see a gold
cuff link anywhere?

933
00:48:34,480 --> 00:48:35,674
No, sorry.

934
00:48:35,748 --> 00:48:37,215
Hey, Frank.

935
00:48:37,283 --> 00:48:39,376
My wife is going
to slit my throat.

936
00:48:39,451 --> 00:48:40,748
I'll keep my eye out.

937
00:48:40,819 --> 00:48:42,446
Thanks.

938
00:48:43,756 --> 00:48:44,916
- Hi, June.
- Sorry we're late.

939
00:48:44,990 --> 00:48:46,287
Someone forgot a present,

940
00:48:46,358 --> 00:48:48,588
so I said I wouldn't
show up empty-handed.

941
00:48:48,661 --> 00:48:49,923
Oh, you're sweet.
Thank you.

942
00:48:49,995 --> 00:48:51,485
Joey, take this,
put this on the table.

943
00:48:51,564 --> 00:48:52,895
- Patty.
- How you doing?

944
00:48:52,965 --> 00:48:54,899
- Sorry, I need a drink.
- That's all right.

945
00:48:54,967 --> 00:48:56,332
Now... now I'm a coat rack?

946
00:48:56,402 --> 00:48:57,960
Yeah...

947
00:48:58,037 --> 00:48:59,595
What's going on with the wig?

948
00:48:59,672 --> 00:49:01,105
Eh, she got it Third Street.

949
00:49:01,173 --> 00:49:02,504
Oh.

950
00:49:02,575 --> 00:49:05,738
Hey, listen, um, here's a little
something for the boy.

951
00:49:05,811 --> 00:49:06,869
Oh, Sal.

952
00:49:06,946 --> 00:49:07,913
Oh, Patty.

953
00:49:07,980 --> 00:49:10,210
<i>Come on, he's like a son to me.
Buy him a car.</i>

954
00:49:10,282 --> 00:49:11,214
First he goes to college.

955
00:49:11,283 --> 00:49:12,307
No, he doesn't need college.

956
00:49:12,384 --> 00:49:13,316
He's got me.

957
00:49:15,421 --> 00:49:16,683
You know something,

958
00:49:16,755 --> 00:49:18,746
if I was a little less honorable, uh,

959
00:49:18,824 --> 00:49:20,086
I'd have taken Frank out

960
00:49:20,159 --> 00:49:21,717
the first day I laid eyes on you.

961
00:49:21,794 --> 00:49:23,625
If you were
a more honorable guy...

962
00:49:23,696 --> 00:49:25,129
Hey, be nice.

963
00:49:25,197 --> 00:49:26,221
Okay? Relax.

964
00:49:26,298 --> 00:49:28,198
Take a breath and get
the look off your face.

965
00:49:28,267 --> 00:49:29,234
What look, Sal?

966
00:49:29,301 --> 00:49:31,292
Be nice, tough guy.

967
00:49:32,338 --> 00:49:34,329
I apologize, Sal.

968
00:49:34,406 --> 00:49:35,668
All right.
All right.

969
00:49:35,741 --> 00:49:37,140
Enough about honor.

970
00:49:37,209 --> 00:49:39,609
Go make a plate, and you
take this for me, okay.

971
00:49:39,678 --> 00:49:41,612
Thank you for coming, Sal.

972
00:49:41,680 --> 00:49:43,238
Thank you.

973
00:49:43,315 --> 00:49:44,577
<i>They broke the law,</i>

974
00:49:44,650 --> 00:49:46,550
<i>but they owned the neighborhood.</i>

975
00:49:46,619 --> 00:49:48,553
<i>Joey never bought it,</i>

976
00:49:48,621 --> 00:49:51,920
<i>but from where I sat,
it seemed like a pretty good trade.</i>

977
00:49:51,991 --> 00:49:53,959
<i>The part I didn't get</i>

978
00:49:54,026 --> 00:49:56,256
<i>was that we were all paying a price:</i>

979
00:49:56,328 --> 00:49:58,228
<i>Me...</i>

980
00:49:58,297 --> 00:49:59,662
<i>Mouse...</i>

981
00:49:59,732 --> 00:50:01,825
<i>even the innocent bystanders,</i>

982
00:50:01,900 --> 00:50:03,868
<i>- Hey, Mouse!
- like the guy who sold us groceries.</i>

983
00:50:03,936 --> 00:50:06,200
Want to see something?

984
00:50:06,272 --> 00:50:08,206
Nino?

985
00:50:08,274 --> 00:50:10,265
Nino...

986
00:50:11,877 --> 00:50:13,811
You shouldn't be here.

987
00:50:13,879 --> 00:50:16,643
Get out of here.

988
00:50:42,308 --> 00:50:43,297
Mr. Gallo?

989
00:50:52,851 --> 00:50:54,614
Hey!

990
00:50:56,221 --> 00:50:58,348
We tried to find out what
he was doing there,

991
00:50:58,424 --> 00:51:00,449
and he clamped right up.

992
00:51:00,526 --> 00:51:02,118
Kept on saying, however,

993
00:51:02,194 --> 00:51:04,128
that he was a friend of yours,

994
00:51:04,196 --> 00:51:06,130
and that's all we could get.

995
00:51:06,198 --> 00:51:08,723
I've been a friend
of the Montanari family

996
00:51:08,801 --> 00:51:11,326
for many years.

997
00:51:15,174 --> 00:51:17,165
He had this in his pocket.

998
00:51:19,278 --> 00:51:21,337
Of course he wouldn't
say where it came from.

999
00:51:23,182 --> 00:51:25,173
I'd like to know...

1000
00:51:26,185 --> 00:51:28,176
...how he found that body.

1001
00:51:31,290 --> 00:51:32,416
Hmm?

1002
00:51:41,633 --> 00:51:43,567
Watch your fingers.

1003
00:51:43,635 --> 00:51:46,570
What the hell were
you doing out there?

1004
00:51:46,638 --> 00:51:48,196
Answer me, Nino.

1005
00:51:48,273 --> 00:51:49,706
What were you doing
out there?

1006
00:51:49,775 --> 00:51:50,707
Nothing.

1007
00:51:50,776 --> 00:51:52,073
A dead body is not nothing.

1008
00:51:52,144 --> 00:51:54,339
And don't you ever
use my name with the police.

1009
00:51:54,413 --> 00:51:55,573
What's the matter with you?

1010
00:51:55,647 --> 00:51:56,773
You know those guys.

1011
00:51:56,849 --> 00:51:58,009
Say they do favors for you.

1012
00:51:58,083 --> 00:52:00,051
You want me to go to jail
for the rest of my life?

1013
00:52:00,119 --> 00:52:01,916
- Is that what you want?
- All right, all right.

1014
00:52:01,987 --> 00:52:03,648
Did you steal Carmine's cuff links?

1015
00:52:03,722 --> 00:52:06,247
You steal.

1016
00:52:06,325 --> 00:52:07,485
I'm telling you, Nino,

1017
00:52:07,559 --> 00:52:08,924
I'm telling you right now,

1018
00:52:08,994 --> 00:52:10,621
if I get caught up
in this mess,

1019
00:52:10,696 --> 00:52:11,924
I'm going to kick your ass.

1020
00:52:11,997 --> 00:52:13,965
You lay one hand on my kid,

1021
00:52:14,032 --> 00:52:15,465
and I will cut it off.

1022
00:52:15,534 --> 00:52:17,161
It's for his own good.

1023
00:52:20,973 --> 00:52:24,773
How did you know
about the body?

1024
00:52:28,781 --> 00:52:30,772
I don't want you
taking risks like that.

1025
00:52:33,519 --> 00:52:35,783
Why did he die?

1026
00:52:38,924 --> 00:52:40,858
I'm not sure.

1027
00:52:49,268 --> 00:52:53,034
I didn't take those, by the way.
Just for the record.

1028
00:52:53,105 --> 00:52:55,938
It must seem kind of strange,

1029
00:52:56,008 --> 00:52:57,976
me asking to see you
after all these years.

1030
00:52:58,043 --> 00:53:00,034
I'm glad you did.

1031
00:53:02,014 --> 00:53:03,948
My son got in trouble
the other day.

1032
00:53:04,016 --> 00:53:05,040
Yeah, I know.

1033
00:53:05,117 --> 00:53:06,277
He's a good kid.

1034
00:53:06,351 --> 00:53:07,943
I'm sure he is.

1035
00:53:08,020 --> 00:53:10,955
Well, I was just hoping that...

1036
00:53:11,023 --> 00:53:13,457
maybe you can keep an eye out,

1037
00:53:13,525 --> 00:53:15,959
and let me know if there's
something I should know.

1038
00:53:16,028 --> 00:53:17,461
Sure.

1039
00:53:17,529 --> 00:53:19,121
Really?
Yeah, absolutely.

1040
00:53:19,198 --> 00:53:20,290
Oh, that's great.

1041
00:53:20,365 --> 00:53:22,299
- Thanks.
- Yeah.

1042
00:53:22,367 --> 00:53:23,698
I appreciate it.

1043
00:53:23,769 --> 00:53:25,236
Hey, Patty.

1044
00:53:25,304 --> 00:53:27,670
That grocer, Gallo...
He was a friend of yours, right?

1045
00:53:27,739 --> 00:53:29,764
Well, I wouldn't say
