1046
00:53:29,842 --> 00:53:31,810
- He was my grocer.
- Right.

1047
00:53:31,877 --> 00:53:33,276
You know why he was murdered?

1048
00:53:33,345 --> 00:53:34,937
No.

1049
00:53:35,013 --> 00:53:37,174
Yeah.
He got into it with some kid,

1050
00:53:37,249 --> 00:53:40,184
selling drugs out front
of his store.

1051
00:53:40,252 --> 00:53:41,844
Oh...

1052
00:53:41,920 --> 00:53:43,353
No, that's impossible.

1053
00:53:43,422 --> 00:53:45,617
They don't sell drugs.

1054
00:53:45,691 --> 00:53:47,852
Looks like Mouse is selling to me.
What do you think?

1055
00:53:50,028 --> 00:53:53,395
Well, I mean, if he is,
Frank doesn't know about it.

1056
00:53:53,465 --> 00:53:55,399
They're liars, Patty.

1057
00:53:55,467 --> 00:53:56,866
They are liars,
and they're killers.

1058
00:53:56,935 --> 00:53:58,960
That's how they get by.

1059
00:54:02,508 --> 00:54:04,271
Frank!

1060
00:54:04,343 --> 00:54:05,571
Where is he?
Is he here?

1061
00:54:05,644 --> 00:54:06,941
- He's upstairs in the apartment.
- Frank!

1062
00:54:07,012 --> 00:54:08,639
Hey, what's going on?

1063
00:54:08,714 --> 00:54:10,682
- What are you doing here?
- Where's your son?

1064
00:54:10,749 --> 00:54:13,309
- Hey, you know better to come to my...
- He's a drug dealer, Frank!

1065
00:54:13,385 --> 00:54:15,444
- What are you talking about?
- I need him to stay away...

1066
00:54:15,521 --> 00:54:16,988
Hey, we're in the middle
of dinner here.

1067
00:54:17,055 --> 00:54:19,615
- You stay away from my kid!
- Hey, hey. Hold on second, hey!

1068
00:54:19,691 --> 00:54:20,783
- He's garbage!
- Will you control yourself?

1069
00:54:20,859 --> 00:54:21,985
Do not come near my son!

1070
00:54:22,060 --> 00:54:23,459
- Take it easy.
- He's a drug dealer!

1071
00:54:23,529 --> 00:54:25,087
Your son.

1072
00:54:25,163 --> 00:54:26,960
Selling drugs to kids
in our neighborhood.

1073
00:54:27,032 --> 00:54:27,999
She's lying.

1074
00:54:28,066 --> 00:54:28,998
I saw pictures...

1075
00:54:29,067 --> 00:54:30,261
FBI surveillance...

1076
00:54:30,335 --> 00:54:31,768
of him at the grocery store.

1077
00:54:31,837 --> 00:54:33,099
Pictures?
How'd you see pictures?

1078
00:54:33,171 --> 00:54:34,365
They brought me in
for questioning.

1079
00:54:34,439 --> 00:54:36,805
He's all over them.

1080
00:54:39,278 --> 00:54:41,371
- Are you selling?
- No.

1081
00:54:41,446 --> 00:54:43,676
Did you hear what she just said?

1082
00:54:43,749 --> 00:54:45,011
Yeah, I heard.
She doesn't know...

1083
00:54:45,083 --> 00:54:47,847
- They got pictures, you understand?
- Yeah, but, Dad...

1084
00:54:50,556 --> 00:54:52,751
- Frank!
- I told you.

1085
00:54:52,824 --> 00:54:54,621
I told you to come to me.

1086
00:54:54,693 --> 00:54:57,594
I told you!
What's wrong with you?

1087
00:54:59,798 --> 00:55:01,527
There's one thing
you had to do...

1088
00:55:01,600 --> 00:55:05,434
just one thing... is stay clean.

1089
00:55:05,504 --> 00:55:06,732
Just one thing!

1090
00:55:06,805 --> 00:55:08,602
Stay clean.
That's all I ever asked of you.

1091
00:55:08,674 --> 00:55:09,902
- Frank, let him go.
- I'm sorry.

1092
00:55:09,975 --> 00:55:11,340
- No. Where were you?
- Enough, enough.

1093
00:55:11,410 --> 00:55:13,401
Where were you?
You're supposed to keep an eye on him.

1094
00:55:13,478 --> 00:55:14,775
- You keep telling me he's clean.
- Enough!

1095
00:55:14,846 --> 00:55:16,837
Enough for now!

1096
00:55:16,915 --> 00:55:18,507
You be quiet.

1097
00:55:18,584 --> 00:55:22,350
How dare you come here
like you got the right.

1098
00:55:22,421 --> 00:55:24,912
It's not enough,
your fancy apartment, your fancy car,

1099
00:55:24,990 --> 00:55:26,457
my husband
seven nights a week?

1100
00:55:26,525 --> 00:55:28,220
Get the hell out of my house.

1101
00:55:28,293 --> 00:55:29,590
Patty, go home.

1102
00:55:29,661 --> 00:55:31,322
Get out!

1103
00:55:36,134 --> 00:55:37,533
<i>Once you start paying attention,</i>

1104
00:55:37,603 --> 00:55:40,094
<i>change happens very fast.</i>

1105
00:55:40,172 --> 00:55:42,504
<i>You see evidence
everywhere you turn,:</i>

1106
00:55:42,574 --> 00:55:45,975
<i>Signs you've been missing
for weeks, maybe years.</i>

1107
00:55:46,044 --> 00:55:49,275
<i>No place is safe,
not even your own home.</i>

1108
00:55:49,348 --> 00:55:51,976
<i>Every act of kindness hides a threat,</i>

1109
00:55:52,050 --> 00:55:55,952
<i>every friend becomes an enemy.</i>

1110
00:56:01,293 --> 00:56:04,524
<i>There's no one to turn to,
and no going back.</i>

1111
00:56:04,596 --> 00:56:09,363
<i>The deed is done,
your soul is sold.</i>

1112
00:56:09,434 --> 00:56:12,335
So, Patty, you're heading up
to Canada, right?

1113
00:56:12,404 --> 00:56:13,598
Uh, yeah.

1114
00:56:13,672 --> 00:56:15,970
I'm actually leaving
in about an hour.

1115
00:56:16,041 --> 00:56:18,202
Sal wants you to take June.

1116
00:56:18,276 --> 00:56:19,868
June?

1117
00:56:19,945 --> 00:56:21,970
She's getting a little jumpy
from all the attention.

1118
00:56:22,047 --> 00:56:23,378
He needs to distract her.

1119
00:56:23,448 --> 00:56:25,416
Is he crazy?
I can't take June.

1120
00:56:25,484 --> 00:56:27,679
It's one time.

1121
00:56:27,753 --> 00:56:29,550
Two girls on a shopping trip.
You'll be fine.

1122
00:56:29,621 --> 00:56:31,782
Do you know how many
times I say that?

1123
00:56:31,857 --> 00:56:33,290
"I'll be fine."

1124
00:56:33,358 --> 00:56:34,985
And then I throw up.

1125
00:56:35,060 --> 00:56:36,857
Don't get all dramatic
on me, honey.

1126
00:56:36,928 --> 00:56:38,657
No, Jimmy.

1127
00:56:38,730 --> 00:56:40,061
I'm serious.

1128
00:56:40,132 --> 00:56:42,362
I can't... I can't keep doing this.

1129
00:56:42,434 --> 00:56:44,299
I got to get out.

1130
00:56:44,369 --> 00:56:46,837
I got to take my kids
and move someplace safe.

1131
00:56:46,905 --> 00:56:48,998
Nobody gets out.

1132
00:56:49,074 --> 00:56:51,008
We're like a retirement home...

1133
00:56:51,076 --> 00:56:53,203
you just get old,
and then you die.

1134
00:56:53,278 --> 00:56:54,973
Simple as that.

1135
00:56:55,047 --> 00:56:57,038
It's a good life.

1136
00:57:01,119 --> 00:57:02,950
15 agents,
right outside my house.

1137
00:57:03,021 --> 00:57:04,249
<i>Can you believe it?</i>

1138
00:57:04,322 --> 00:57:06,381
Haven't had fun in,
like, three days.

1139
00:57:07,793 --> 00:57:10,227
So who was this guy, anyway?

1140
00:57:10,295 --> 00:57:12,195
A grocer.

1141
00:57:12,264 --> 00:57:14,994
Oh, God, you would've thought
he was the G.D. Pope.

1142
00:57:16,134 --> 00:57:19,365
June, what are you
doing to yourself?

1143
00:57:20,439 --> 00:57:22,134
- What?
- What? What?

1144
00:57:22,207 --> 00:57:23,731
The coke.
What do you think?

1145
00:57:23,809 --> 00:57:26,073
I'm just trying to have
a little fun, all right?

1146
00:57:26,144 --> 00:57:28,305
Well, you're gonna, you're gonna
have to throw that stuff away

1147
00:57:28,380 --> 00:57:29,540
before we get to the border.

1148
00:57:30,615 --> 00:57:33,083
I'm not throwing this out.

1149
00:57:33,151 --> 00:57:34,641
Yeah, you are, June.

1150
00:57:34,720 --> 00:57:36,210
No, I'm not.

1151
00:57:36,288 --> 00:57:38,153
Okay, look, we're going
to the border.

1152
00:57:38,223 --> 00:57:39,815
I'm trying to have fun
on this trip.

1153
00:57:39,891 --> 00:57:41,017
I haven't had any fun.

1154
00:57:41,093 --> 00:57:42,890
Will you just let me
have some fun?

1155
00:57:42,961 --> 00:57:44,394
What are you doing?
What...

1156
00:57:47,532 --> 00:57:49,056
Here's another one for you.

1157
00:57:49,134 --> 00:57:50,328
Let's try this.

1158
00:57:50,402 --> 00:57:52,996
Oh, yes.

1159
00:57:55,273 --> 00:57:59,903
Oh... oh...

1160
00:57:59,978 --> 00:58:01,240
Ooh, I will take it.

1161
00:58:01,313 --> 00:58:02,337
Oh, good.

1162
00:58:02,414 --> 00:58:04,143
I'll wrap it up for you.

1163
00:58:04,216 --> 00:58:06,343
It is nice, you have to admit.

1164
00:58:12,724 --> 00:58:14,749
Who the hell is that guy?

1165
00:58:14,826 --> 00:58:16,088
I saw him at the border.

1166
00:58:16,161 --> 00:58:18,026
<i>Could I get whacked
for fooling around?</i>

1167
00:58:18,096 --> 00:58:19,893
- I gotta go.
- Now?

1168
00:58:19,965 --> 00:58:22,456
Listen, just pay for the coat

1169
00:58:22,534 --> 00:58:23,967
and meet me at the hotel.

1170
00:58:24,035 --> 00:58:26,162
Do me a favor,
do not talk to that guy.

1171
00:58:26,238 --> 00:58:27,170
But I haven't...

1172
00:58:27,239 --> 00:58:29,104
Don't talk to him.

1173
00:58:34,479 --> 00:58:36,538
How about some hats?

1174
00:58:57,402 --> 00:58:58,391
An agent?

1175
00:58:58,470 --> 00:58:59,994
Yeah, trying to look like tourist.

1176
00:59:00,071 --> 00:59:02,266
Or maybe he was a tourist.

1177
00:59:02,340 --> 00:59:04,240
I think he followed me
across the border.

1178
00:59:04,309 --> 00:59:06,174
That's a pretty active imagination.

1179
00:59:06,244 --> 00:59:09,008
All right, just give me the money
so I can get out of here.

1180
00:59:09,080 --> 00:59:10,638
You're early.

1181
00:59:10,715 --> 00:59:11,977
Montreal doesn't deliver till tomorrow.

1182
00:59:12,050 --> 00:59:14,848
Okay, then give me what you got.

1183
00:59:16,721 --> 00:59:18,951
Do you want to call Sal
or should I?

1184
00:59:31,469 --> 00:59:34,870
I knew it was a mistake
to use a broad.

1185
00:59:34,940 --> 00:59:36,601
You should get out.

1186
00:59:36,675 --> 00:59:39,007
You should think about
a helping profession.

1187
00:59:39,077 --> 00:59:40,510
Like nursing.

1188
00:59:41,680 --> 00:59:42,772
Police!

1189
00:59:48,286 --> 00:59:50,049
Freeze!

1190
00:59:50,121 --> 00:59:51,179
Hands on the counter!

1191
00:59:52,190 --> 00:59:54,715
- Where's the money?
- What money?

1192
00:59:54,793 --> 00:59:56,317
Wrong answer!

1193
00:59:56,394 --> 00:59:58,259
Keep an eye on her.

1194
00:59:58,330 --> 01:00:00,389
Let's go.

1195
01:00:00,465 --> 01:00:02,899
Ma'am, are you okay?

1196
01:00:02,968 --> 01:00:04,902
I think I'm going
to throw up.

1197
01:00:04,970 --> 01:00:08,030
- Uh...
- Is there a bathroom?

1198
01:00:08,106 --> 01:00:09,767
This way.

1199
01:00:17,215 --> 01:00:19,809
- Right here.
- Okay.

1200
01:00:53,852 --> 01:00:55,479
What the hell's going on?

1201
01:00:55,553 --> 01:00:56,485
Where is she?

1202
01:00:56,554 --> 01:00:57,680
She's in the washroom.

1203
01:00:57,756 --> 01:00:59,246
Are you out of your mind?

1204
01:01:01,993 --> 01:01:03,620
There's another door!

1205
01:01:09,301 --> 01:01:11,269
Where the hell have you been?
I'm bored out of my mind.

1206
01:01:11,336 --> 01:01:12,803
- Get dressed.
- We better be going

1207
01:01:12,871 --> 01:01:14,805
- somewhere nice for dinner.
- We're checking out.

1208
01:01:14,873 --> 01:01:15,862
Dressed?

1209
01:01:24,582 --> 01:01:26,106
Are we in trouble?

1210
01:01:26,184 --> 01:01:28,277
We can't go back together.

1211
01:01:28,353 --> 01:01:29,911
I need you
to carry the money.

1212
01:01:29,988 --> 01:01:31,819
I can't.

1213
01:01:31,890 --> 01:01:33,551
Oh, yes, you can.

1214
01:01:33,625 --> 01:01:35,320
You're gonna take these,

1215
01:01:35,393 --> 01:01:36,883
you're gonna wrap
the money to your body,

1216
01:01:36,962 --> 01:01:38,930
and then you're gonna put
your clothes on over it.

1217
01:01:38,997 --> 01:01:40,965
I've done it 50 times;
nobody's ever caught me.

1218
01:01:41,032 --> 01:01:42,465
Once you get
across the border,

1219
01:01:42,534 --> 01:01:44,263
go to your apartment,

1220
01:01:44,336 --> 01:01:47,271
and then... and then call me
at the club, all right?

1221
01:01:47,339 --> 01:01:49,307
No, I'm not kidding,
Patty, okay? I can't.

1222
01:01:49,374 --> 01:01:50,602
I'll go crazy,

1223
01:01:50,675 --> 01:01:52,973
or I'll start crying
or some crap like that.

1224
01:01:53,044 --> 01:01:54,875
- I mean, they'll arrest me, and then...
- Listen to me.

1225
01:01:54,946 --> 01:01:58,040
I don't have time for this.

1226
01:01:58,116 --> 01:02:00,914
If we don't get that money home,

1227
01:02:00,986 --> 01:02:03,784
we're both dead.

1228
01:02:07,425 --> 01:02:10,155
Okay.

1229
01:02:10,228 --> 01:02:13,994
Okay, we're gonna be okay.

1230
01:02:22,741 --> 01:02:23,673
- Any day.
- Gin.

1231
01:02:23,742 --> 01:02:24,970
What do you mean gin?

1232
01:02:25,043 --> 01:02:27,511
What are you doing? Come on.

1233
01:02:27,579 --> 01:02:29,069
Gin.

1234
01:02:29,147 --> 01:02:31,138
- Get out of here.
- What are you talking about?

1235
01:02:31,216 --> 01:02:33,013
- That is gin.
- It means I win.

1236
01:02:33,084 --> 01:02:34,346
No, it means you cheat.

1237
01:02:34,419 --> 01:02:36,011
I do not cheat.
How does he get gin?

1238
01:02:36,087 --> 01:02:37,577
I do not cheat.

1239
01:02:37,655 --> 01:02:39,748
Hey, hello to you, too.

1240
01:02:39,824 --> 01:02:41,553
- Hey, Patty, how are you?
- Hey, Patty.

1241
01:02:41,626 --> 01:02:42,854
You're early.

1242
01:02:42,927 --> 01:02:45,589
Something came up.

1243
01:02:45,663 --> 01:02:47,096
Deal me out.

1244
01:02:47,165 --> 01:02:48,723
All right, I'm dealer.
Who's dealer, me?

1245
01:02:48,800 --> 01:02:50,392
Yeah, do it.

1246
01:02:50,468 --> 01:02:52,368
What do you mean
something came up?

1247
01:02:52,437 --> 01:02:54,098
They got busted.

1248
01:02:54,172 --> 01:02:56,436
Busted how?

1249
01:02:56,508 --> 01:02:58,567
Hey, Patty, how did you slip the G?

1250
01:03:01,546 --> 01:03:02,945
What happened to the money?

1251
01:03:03,014 --> 01:03:04,242
June has it.

1252
01:03:04,315 --> 01:03:06,510
You gave the money to June?

1253
01:03:06,584 --> 01:03:10,577
Yeah, I don't know if you've noticed,
but there's FBI agents everywhere we go.

1254
01:03:10,655 --> 01:03:11,781
Where is she?

1255
01:03:11,856 --> 01:03:13,016
She's on her way home.

1256
01:03:13,091 --> 01:03:14,183
Then why aren't you with her?

1257
01:03:14,259 --> 01:03:16,386
I'm waiting here for her to call me.

1258
01:03:16,461 --> 01:03:19,487
No, no, you don't wait here.
You stay with her.

1259
01:03:19,564 --> 01:03:22,032
And you sit on the steps
all day, if you have to.

1260
01:03:22,100 --> 01:03:24,227
You know what, Frank?
Don't tell me what to do.

1261
01:03:24,302 --> 01:03:25,428
While you're waiting here,

1262
01:03:25,503 --> 01:03:28,438
she's helping herself to the cash
and keeping up with her drug habit.

1263
01:03:28,506 --> 01:03:31,202
You know what? I been doing this
for six years without your help.

1264
01:03:31,276 --> 01:03:33,369
Is that what you want me to tell Sal?

1265
01:03:33,445 --> 01:03:36,278
No, you know what?
You can tell Sal to go to hell.

1266
01:03:36,347 --> 01:03:38,577
<i>Hey, Frankie, take it easy. Come on.</i>

1267
01:03:38,650 --> 01:03:40,208
What?

1268
01:03:40,285 --> 01:03:41,582
It's not her fault.

1269
01:03:41,653 --> 01:03:42,745
Excuse me?

1270
01:03:42,821 --> 01:03:44,789
It's not her fault.

1271
01:03:46,691 --> 01:03:50,525
Did I ask your opinion, Bones?
Did I?

1272
01:03:58,136 --> 01:04:00,764
What?

1273
01:04:21,459 --> 01:04:23,859
Oh, my God.
Sweetie, what happened to you?

1274
01:04:23,928 --> 01:04:26,692
My father, he was a little upset.

1275
01:04:26,764 --> 01:04:27,890
<i>Can I come in, Patty?</i>

1276
01:04:27,966 --> 01:04:30,560
Yeah, yeah, come in.

1277
01:04:33,738 --> 01:04:35,103
Oh...

1278
01:04:35,173 --> 01:04:36,470
I'm in trouble, Patty.

1279
01:04:36,541 --> 01:04:38,600
I think Palmeri's going to kill me.

1280
01:04:38,676 --> 01:04:41,167
No, no. Nobody's going to kill you.

1281
01:04:41,246 --> 01:04:42,645
It's my fault.

1282
01:04:42,714 --> 01:04:45,808
The drugs... Gallo...

1283
01:04:45,884 --> 01:04:48,284
the Feds tightening up on us.

1284
01:04:48,353 --> 01:04:50,583
Why would Palmeri
be afraid of the Feds?

1285
01:04:50,655 --> 01:04:53,715
I don't know.
I was hoping you could talk to him,

1286
01:04:53,791 --> 01:04:57,022
remind him how much my father
does for the family.

1287
01:04:57,095 --> 01:04:59,893
Sweetie, I think it'll sound better
coming from your father.

1288
01:05:01,666 --> 01:05:03,725
I don't have much pull
with him right now.

1289
01:05:03,801 --> 01:05:05,393
Look, he was upset

1290
01:05:05,470 --> 01:05:09,236
because he loves you
and he cares about you.

1291
01:05:09,307 --> 01:05:12,105
Okay, go to him. He'll help you.

1292
01:05:12,177 --> 01:05:13,667
Yeah, sure.

1293
01:05:15,647 --> 01:05:17,046
Okay.

1294
01:05:21,819 --> 01:05:24,481
I never meant
to get Nino in trouble.

1295
01:05:24,556 --> 01:05:26,046
I'm sorry, Patty.

1296
01:05:26,124 --> 01:05:27,785
It's okay.

1297
01:05:42,807 --> 01:05:46,243
Don't you ever backtalk me
in front of my crew.

1298
01:05:46,311 --> 01:05:49,007
Like you got me
on some kind of leash.

1299
01:05:49,080 --> 01:05:50,138
Did you beat up Mouse?

1300
01:05:50,215 --> 01:05:52,809
You did, didn't ya?

1301
01:05:52,884 --> 01:05:55,409
Kicked him like a dog,
your own son.

1302
01:05:55,486 --> 01:05:59,217
You know, you're beginning
to sound like my wife.

1303
01:05:59,290 --> 01:06:01,622
Frank, he's scared.
He thinks Sal's gonna kill him.

1304
01:06:01,693 --> 01:06:02,717
Well, maybe he's right.

1305
01:06:02,794 --> 01:06:04,159
Well, then you need
to do something.

1306
01:06:04,229 --> 01:06:06,254
Yeah? What do you want me to do?
You tell me.

1307
01:06:06,331 --> 01:06:07,593
Go to Sal!

1308
01:06:07,665 --> 01:06:10,156
Why you keep talking
about Mouse?

1309
01:06:10,235 --> 01:06:13,830
Because he came here asking
for help, Frank.

1310
01:06:19,310 --> 01:06:20,607
Mouse came here?

1311
01:06:20,678 --> 01:06:22,168
Why would he come to you?

1312
01:06:22,247 --> 01:06:24,875
Because instead of acting
like his father, you beat him up.

1313
01:06:24,949 --> 01:06:27,042
Well, tell me something.

1314
01:06:27,118 --> 01:06:28,847
Is there something going on
between you two?

1315
01:06:28,920 --> 01:06:30,046
Oh, my...

1316
01:06:30,121 --> 01:06:33,090
No, don't you turn away from me!
I asked you a question!

1317
01:06:33,157 --> 01:06:34,681
You keep your hands off my mother!

1318
01:06:34,759 --> 01:06:37,489
Hey, don't you touch him!

1319
01:06:39,664 --> 01:06:40,892
Get out of my house!

1320
01:06:50,441 --> 01:06:51,373
Sweetie, I'm sorry.

1321
01:06:51,442 --> 01:06:53,637
I'm okay. Look at me.
I'm okay.

1322
01:06:53,711 --> 01:06:56,612
Why do you always got to defend him?

1323
01:06:59,617 --> 01:07:01,084
<i>Come here.</i>

1324
01:07:01,152 --> 01:07:03,746
<i>Come here, sweetheart.</i>

1325
01:07:12,930 --> 01:07:14,420
You're always talking
about family.

1326
01:07:14,499 --> 01:07:16,558
Family this, family that.

1327
01:07:16,634 --> 01:07:19,296
I told you they're not family.

1328
01:07:19,370 --> 01:07:22,271
Ma, please don't start with me.

1329
01:07:53,204 --> 01:07:56,935
Hey, how come
you weren't inside?

1330
01:07:59,644 --> 01:08:02,943
You having some problems
with Frank?

1331
01:08:08,052 --> 01:08:12,386
Mouse came to me for help,
and I sent him away.

1332
01:08:12,457 --> 01:08:14,891
Mouse is too far gone.

1333
01:08:14,959 --> 01:08:17,689
Nobody could have helped him.

1334
01:08:17,762 --> 01:08:21,698
Maybe.

1335
01:08:21,766 --> 01:08:24,633
I want you to wear a wire, Patty.

1336
01:08:24,702 --> 01:08:26,670
Palmeri's cleaning house.

1337
01:08:26,738 --> 01:08:29,707
I'd like to stop him before he
gets rid of somebody else.

1338
01:08:29,774 --> 01:08:32,334
I just need to hear somebody say
that Palmeri ordered the hit.

1339
01:08:32,410 --> 01:08:35,641
That's it.

1340
01:08:35,713 --> 01:08:39,308
And when it's over,
we'll take care of you.

1341
01:08:39,384 --> 01:08:43,514
We'll get you a nice house
someplace out of the city,

1342
01:08:43,588 --> 01:08:47,080
somewhere your kids
will be safe.

1343
01:08:47,158 --> 01:08:50,059
Sounds so easy.

1344
01:08:50,128 --> 01:08:53,291
Good guys and bad guys...
pick a side.

1345
01:08:53,364 --> 01:08:54,331
They're criminals.

1346
01:08:54,399 --> 01:08:55,696
So am I.
No, you're not.

1347
01:08:55,767 --> 01:08:58,167
You made a mistake.

1348
01:08:58,236 --> 01:09:01,171
Now you got a chance
to make it right.

1349
01:09:01,239 --> 01:09:03,503
These people helped me.

1350
01:09:03,574 --> 01:09:06,407
I made them my family.

1351
01:09:06,477 --> 01:09:08,035
I knew what I was doing.

1352
01:09:08,112 --> 01:09:09,306
You're not the same as they are.

1353
01:09:09,380 --> 01:09:10,847
You don't know.

1354
01:09:10,915 --> 01:09:12,280
I know what I see.

1355
01:09:14,385 --> 01:09:19,345
Hmm. Everybody says that.

1356
01:09:19,424 --> 01:09:22,757
And they all say something different.

1357
01:09:26,330 --> 01:09:28,195
Thanks for the coffee.

1358
01:09:44,615 --> 01:09:47,948
I, uh...

1359
01:09:48,019 --> 01:09:51,819
I got these when he was born.

1360
01:09:51,889 --> 01:09:54,084
500 bucks a box.

1361
01:09:54,158 --> 01:09:56,524
I was passing them out like candy.

1362
01:10:00,598 --> 01:10:02,225
Frank, I'm sorry.

1363
01:10:03,267 --> 01:10:04,598
I really am.

1364
01:10:08,105 --> 01:10:09,936
I, uh, I can't go home.

1365
01:10:10,007 --> 01:10:11,440
Mary's cleaning up the house.

1366
01:10:11,509 --> 01:10:14,740
The cupboards, the drawers,
the floors, everything.

1367
01:10:14,812 --> 01:10:16,837
Smells like a morgue.

1368
01:10:20,685 --> 01:10:22,676
Don't look at me like that.

1369
01:10:22,753 --> 01:10:26,917
Like what?

1370
01:10:26,991 --> 01:10:30,825
Like you hate me.

1371
01:10:30,895 --> 01:10:32,624
I don't hate you, Frank.

1372
01:10:38,569 --> 01:10:40,332
I could never hurt you.

1373
01:10:43,975 --> 01:10:46,500
You know that, right?

1374
01:10:46,577 --> 01:10:50,877
You're inside me all the time.

1375
01:11:57,548 --> 01:11:59,948
What's going on?
Why do you have a gun?

1376
01:12:00,017 --> 01:12:01,848
I'm next, Patty.
Palmeri blames me.

1377
01:12:01,919 --> 01:12:03,318
Will you turn it off?

1378
01:12:03,387 --> 01:12:05,514
What do you mean he blames you?
What do you...

1379
01:12:05,590 --> 01:12:07,581
Because of Mouse. He's my kid!

1380
01:12:07,658 --> 01:12:09,125
Just follow orders.

1381
01:12:09,193 --> 01:12:11,161
Honor, huh?

1382
01:12:11,228 --> 01:12:13,162
Follow orders.

1383
01:12:13,230 --> 01:12:14,993
Okay, Frank,
I don't know what's going on,

1384
01:12:15,066 --> 01:12:16,465
but you gotta get out of here.

1385
01:12:16,534 --> 01:12:18,764
No! No, what are you talking
about, "get out of here"?

1386
01:12:18,836 --> 01:12:21,168
- I have two boys I have to protect.
- I understand that!

1387
01:12:21,238 --> 01:12:22,603
You're walking around
with a shotgun!

1388
01:12:22,673 --> 01:12:24,436
Patty, I got it all worked out, okay?

1389
01:12:24,508 --> 01:12:27,909
Got a friend owes me a favor.

1390
01:12:27,979 --> 01:12:29,469
I want you to call him, okay?

1391
01:12:29,547 --> 01:12:31,447
Ask for plane tickets
someplace warm.

1392
01:12:31,515 --> 01:12:32,482
I don't even care.

1393
01:12:32,550 --> 01:12:33,482
It's over, Frank.

1394
01:12:33,551 --> 01:12:35,280
No, it's for all of us.
It's over.

1395
01:12:35,353 --> 01:12:37,685
I just need some time
to get back on my feet.

1396
01:12:37,755 --> 01:12:39,655
We'll be like we were before,
only even better.

1397
01:12:39,724 --> 01:12:41,749
I promise, baby, okay?

1398
01:12:41,826 --> 01:12:43,316
I promise.

1399
01:12:53,404 --> 01:12:55,338
Hey.

1400
01:12:55,406 --> 01:12:59,103
Patty, holy crap,
you ever hear of a phone?

1401
01:12:59,176 --> 01:13:01,201
I tried calling. You don't answer.

1402
01:13:01,278 --> 01:13:02,973
Yeah, well, I been busy.

1403
01:13:03,047 --> 01:13:04,639
Is Frank in trouble?

1404
01:13:04,715 --> 01:13:06,649
Listen, I can't hang out.

1405
01:13:06,717 --> 01:13:10,016
He thinks there's a hit out on him.
He wants to leave town.

1406
01:13:10,087 --> 01:13:11,554
Yeah, well, maybe he should.

1407
01:13:11,622 --> 01:13:13,055
What is that supposed to mean?

1408
01:13:13,124 --> 01:13:15,558
It means I don't know.

1409
01:13:19,196 --> 01:13:21,687
Oh, June.

1410
01:13:21,766 --> 01:13:24,360
Why would Sal go after Frank?

1411
01:13:24,435 --> 01:13:26,903
'Cause he's completely paranoid.

1412
01:13:26,971 --> 01:13:29,531
Some FBI agent
gave him a nervous breakdown

1413
01:13:29,607 --> 01:13:31,768
saying somebody in the family
gave Mouse those drugs.

1414
01:13:31,842 --> 01:13:32,809
Who would do that?

1415
01:13:32,877 --> 01:13:34,674
It doesn't matter, okay?
Sal is freaking out.

1416
01:13:34,745 --> 01:13:37,680
Last night, I thought
he was gonna kill me.

1417
01:13:37,748 --> 01:13:40,342
Listen, if I were you,
I would go to that club,

1418
01:13:40,418 --> 01:13:42,181
clean out the safe, and walk away.

1419
01:13:42,253 --> 01:13:44,414
That's easier said than done.

1420
01:13:44,488 --> 01:13:45,648
Patty, listen to me.

1421
01:13:45,723 --> 01:13:48,419
It is not just Frank
who's been marked, okay?

1422
01:13:48,492 --> 01:13:49,516
It's you, too.

1423
01:13:52,830 --> 01:13:54,229
I gotta go.

1424
01:13:54,298 --> 01:13:56,789
I'm real sorry.

1425
01:14:38,776 --> 01:14:41,040
Now, if this were a movie...

1426
01:14:41,112 --> 01:14:43,444
and I was watching it,

1427
01:14:43,514 --> 01:14:46,881
I'd say she planned on
taking the money and running.

1428
01:14:46,951 --> 01:14:49,476
Only, see, he got there first

1429
01:14:49,553 --> 01:14:51,885
because he knows
how very smart she is, and...

1430
01:14:51,956 --> 01:14:55,483
well, he has to stay two steps
ahead of her at all times.

1431
01:14:55,559 --> 01:14:57,754
Whatever you're thinking,
you don't have it right.

1432
01:14:57,828 --> 01:15:00,058
You have no idea
what I'm thinking.

1433
01:15:01,732 --> 01:15:03,962
Sal, I've always been loyal to you.

1434
01:15:04,034 --> 01:15:05,501
I might be thinking about, um,

1435
01:15:05,569 --> 01:15:08,504
what it feels like,
maybe, to look down a barrel

1436
01:15:08,572 --> 01:15:10,631
at the end of your life...

1437
01:15:10,708 --> 01:15:14,769
and all those things
that were important to you,

1438
01:15:14,845 --> 01:15:17,040
just knowing you can open
a window, whenever you want,

1439
01:15:17,114 --> 01:15:21,483
and just get to feel
a little rain on your face.

1440
01:15:21,552 --> 01:15:23,884
Frank wasn't helping Mouse.

1441
01:15:23,954 --> 01:15:25,285
He knew what he was doing.

1442
01:15:25,356 --> 01:15:28,985
Okay, but killing him
is not gonna make things better.

1443
01:15:29,059 --> 01:15:32,256
Might send a message, don't you think?

1444
01:15:35,699 --> 01:15:37,189
You told me...

1445
01:15:37,268 --> 01:15:39,668
that the most important thing
in life was family,

1446
01:15:39,737 --> 01:15:40,897
- you remember that?
- That's right.

1447
01:15:40,971 --> 01:15:44,168
If there is no family
there's no trust, trust.

1448
01:15:44,241 --> 01:15:49,269
And on that subject,
I had a little thought:

1449
01:15:49,346 --> 01:15:52,577
Why don't you
take care of Frank,

1450
01:15:52,650 --> 01:15:55,676
put an end to my troubles?

1451
01:15:58,556 --> 01:16:02,048
You... You want me to kill Frank.

1452
01:16:02,126 --> 01:16:05,254
That does sound a little clumsy
when you put it like that.

1453
01:16:05,329 --> 01:16:06,990
You're insane.

1454
01:16:07,064 --> 01:16:11,626
You see, now, Frank,
he was a lot more polite

1455
01:16:11,702 --> 01:16:13,533
when I asked him to do Mouse.

1456
01:16:15,506 --> 01:16:18,566
He was a lot more polite.

1457
01:16:33,123 --> 01:16:34,147
Hey, what'd he say?

1458
01:16:34,225 --> 01:16:36,750
Did you get the tickets?

1459
01:16:39,763 --> 01:16:40,957
What happened?

1460
01:16:41,031 --> 01:16:42,658
You tell me.

1461
01:16:45,002 --> 01:16:47,766
I must have been crazy
to stand up for you.

1462
01:16:47,838 --> 01:16:50,432
What are you talking about?

1463
01:16:52,977 --> 01:16:55,445
Did you kill your son?

1464
01:17:11,762 --> 01:17:15,095
Mouse crossed the line.

1465
01:17:15,165 --> 01:17:18,794
I tried to warn him
a hundred times, Patty.

1466
01:17:22,273 --> 01:17:24,173
He was marked.

1467
01:17:24,241 --> 01:17:27,404
I couldn't give it
to somebody else.

1468
01:17:27,478 --> 01:17:30,242
So he wouldn't suffer...

1469
01:17:32,650 --> 01:17:34,618
so they wouldn't come after you.

1470
01:17:36,754 --> 01:17:39,222
You make me sick.

1471
01:17:40,858 --> 01:17:41,984
Patty.

1472
01:17:52,603 --> 01:17:54,833
Patty, open the door!

1473
01:17:54,905 --> 01:17:57,430
<i>Come on! Come on!
Let's talk about this!</i>

1474
01:17:57,508 --> 01:18:00,306
Open the door, or I'll break it down!

1475
01:18:00,377 --> 01:18:02,937
Patty, come on!

1476
01:18:03,013 --> 01:18:04,947
You're not gonna leave me, Patty!

1477
01:18:05,015 --> 01:18:07,040
You cannot leave me!

1478
01:18:07,117 --> 01:18:09,244
I'll find you!
I'll find you wherever you go!

1479
01:18:09,320 --> 01:18:11,754
You understand?

1480
01:18:11,822 --> 01:18:13,255
Open the door right now!

1481
01:18:13,324 --> 01:18:16,555
Patty, open up!

1482
01:18:16,627 --> 01:18:18,595
Open up right now!

1483
01:18:30,374 --> 01:18:32,934
Mouse...

1484
01:18:57,701 --> 01:19:00,135
Time for school...
up, up, up, up.

1485
01:19:02,072 --> 01:19:05,007
You heard her. Get up.

1486
01:19:35,973 --> 01:19:39,670
Hey, where you going?

1487
01:19:39,743 --> 01:19:41,506
I'm taking the boys to school.

1488
01:19:41,578 --> 01:19:43,409
You're welcome to come.

1489
01:19:43,480 --> 01:19:47,507
No, that's okay.

1490
01:19:47,584 --> 01:19:49,142
Have a good day.

1491
01:20:02,566 --> 01:20:04,693
I thought he wasn't
gonna stay with us anymore.

1492
01:20:04,768 --> 01:20:05,894
Shut up.

1493
01:20:05,969 --> 01:20:07,994
Okay, I need you guys
to do something for me,

1494
01:20:08,072 --> 01:20:10,097
and it's very important.

1495
01:20:10,174 --> 01:20:11,664
Go to class like it's a normal day.

1496
01:20:11,742 --> 01:20:14,905
At 11:30, ask to be excused.
Grandma will be waiting outside.

1497
01:20:14,978 --> 01:20:16,240
If she's not here, do not wait

1498
01:20:16,313 --> 01:20:18,281
even for five minutes,
do you understand?

1499
01:20:18,348 --> 01:20:20,077
This is where you're gonna go.

1500
01:20:20,150 --> 01:20:21,777
Ask to speak to Robert Wilford.

1501
01:20:21,852 --> 01:20:23,342
He'll make sure you're all right.

1502
01:20:23,420 --> 01:20:25,081
That says FBI.

1503
01:20:25,155 --> 01:20:27,623
Yeah, we're not gonna stay
with Frank anymore, sweetie.

1504
01:20:27,691 --> 01:20:28,817
I promise.

1505
01:20:28,892 --> 01:20:32,350
I just need some time to get
some stuff together before we go.

1506
01:20:32,429 --> 01:20:34,420
Yeah. Go where, Ma?

1507
01:20:34,498 --> 01:20:36,625
I don't know. Florida maybe.

1508
01:20:36,700 --> 01:20:37,758
What's happening?

1509
01:20:37,835 --> 01:20:39,097
Okay, sweetie, it's okay.

1510
01:20:39,169 --> 01:20:40,534
Are we gonna be all right?

1511
01:20:40,604 --> 01:20:42,572
Please, I need you to be brave.

1512
01:20:42,639 --> 01:20:45,904
I made some mistakes,
but I'm gonna make it all better, all right?

1513
01:20:45,976 --> 01:20:47,568
Okay.
I love you.

1514
01:20:47,644 --> 01:20:48,611
I love you, too.

1515
01:20:48,679 --> 01:20:49,646
I love you.

1516
01:20:49,713 --> 01:20:51,442
I love you both.

1517
01:20:51,515 --> 01:20:54,348
Take care of your brother, okay?

1518
01:21:02,493 --> 01:21:03,858
Joey, Joey.

1519
01:21:03,927 --> 01:21:05,861
What?

1520
01:21:07,965 --> 01:21:10,024
She has a gun.

1521
01:21:20,177 --> 01:21:23,374
Do you think
she's gonna kill him?

1522
01:21:25,182 --> 01:21:26,774
Ma said we should wait.

1523
01:21:29,319 --> 01:21:31,685
I need to talk to Sal.

1524
01:21:31,755 --> 01:21:35,316
Oh, all nice-nice now
you want to see Sal.

1525
01:21:35,392 --> 01:21:37,792
What if Sal don't want
to see you?

1526
01:21:41,231 --> 01:21:43,222
Oh, come on, you stupid bitch.

1527
01:21:44,535 --> 01:21:46,799
Ho.

1528
01:21:50,374 --> 01:21:52,103
Put down the gun.

1529
01:21:52,176 --> 01:21:56,237
If you want to talk to me,
put it down.

1530
01:22:00,284 --> 01:22:03,219
Where the hell is she?
It's only five minutes away.

1531
01:22:03,287 --> 01:22:04,811
I'd take my time, if I were her.

1532
01:22:29,580 --> 01:22:30,604
Where is she?

1533
01:22:31,915 --> 01:22:33,382
You tell me, Joey.
Where is she?

1534
01:22:33,450 --> 01:22:34,712
I'm calling the police.

1535
01:22:34,785 --> 01:22:36,252
No, you're not.
Give me the phone!

1536
01:22:36,320 --> 01:22:38,584
Let go!
Hey, I asked you a question.

1537
01:22:38,655 --> 01:22:39,587
Where's your mother?

1538
01:22:39,656 --> 01:22:40,816
I don't know where she is!

1539
01:22:40,891 --> 01:22:42,153
Leave him alone!

1540
01:22:43,327 --> 01:22:44,851
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa!

1541
01:22:44,928 --> 01:22:47,419
It's okay.
We're okay, right, Joey?

1542
01:22:47,497 --> 01:22:48,555
You're fine.

1543
01:22:51,435 --> 01:22:52,766
Your dime.

1544
01:22:56,540 --> 01:22:59,134
I spent a lot of time asking myself

1545
01:22:59,209 --> 01:23:02,042
who would've been crazy enough
to work with Mouse,

1546
01:23:02,112 --> 01:23:06,776
risk their whole life
for a few dime bags.

1547
01:23:06,850 --> 01:23:11,253
And then I realized...
it wasn't Frank.

1548
01:23:11,321 --> 01:23:13,585
It wasn't even a guy.

1549
01:23:17,828 --> 01:23:20,763
It was right in front of me
the whole time.

1550
01:23:22,132 --> 01:23:23,827
You gave her drugs
to keep her happy,

1551
01:23:23,900 --> 01:23:27,233
and she found a way
to make a profit on the side.

1552
01:23:27,304 --> 01:23:29,602
And who could
blame her, really?

1553
01:23:29,673 --> 01:23:32,608
Nothing to call your own,
just waiting for the day

1554
01:23:32,676 --> 01:23:34,610
someone turns you in
for a better model.

1555
01:23:36,947 --> 01:23:40,678
Yeah, that sounds very tragic.

1556
01:23:40,751 --> 01:23:45,279
Why you telling me
all this crap, sad story, why?

1557
01:23:45,355 --> 01:23:46,617
What do you want?

1558
01:23:48,992 --> 01:23:51,756
I want to get out.

1559
01:23:51,828 --> 01:23:55,958
I want to take my kids,
and I want to move away.

1560
01:23:56,033 --> 01:24:02,563
And I want you to let Frank live
as long as he leaves me alone.

1561
01:24:02,639 --> 01:24:05,403
So you betray me, and then you
come here and ask for favors.

1562
01:24:05,475 --> 01:24:06,533
No one betrayed you.

1563
01:24:06,610 --> 01:24:09,306
You got this guy living in your house
like a sniveling little child.

1564
01:24:09,379 --> 01:24:11,279
Frank did everything you asked.

1565
01:24:11,348 --> 01:24:13,908
He killed his own son
because you told him to.

1566
01:24:13,984 --> 01:24:14,916
His rules.

1567
01:24:14,985 --> 01:24:19,319
Who broke those rules,
Frank... or you?

1568
01:24:24,494 --> 01:24:26,223
I'm supposed to meet my kids.

1569
01:24:27,898 --> 01:24:30,059
Meeting's not over.

1570
01:24:30,133 --> 01:24:32,158
My kids have a letter.

1571
01:24:32,235 --> 01:24:33,566
If I don't show up,

1572
01:24:33,637 --> 01:24:37,767
all of this information
goes straight to the FBI.

1573
01:24:37,841 --> 01:24:39,536
Of course they have a letter.

1574
01:24:39,609 --> 01:24:42,942
The FBI has tons of letters.

1575
01:24:43,013 --> 01:24:45,311
I'm still here.

1576
01:24:52,556 --> 01:24:56,083
Let's, uh, let's try
to understand one another.

1577
01:24:59,096 --> 01:25:01,894
This has nothing
to do with appearances

1578
01:25:01,965 --> 01:25:08,564
and nothing to do
with even a little bit to do with fear.

1579
01:25:08,638 --> 01:25:13,075
It has everything to do with...
weakness.

1580
01:25:14,244 --> 01:25:18,408
My weakness.

1581
01:25:18,482 --> 01:25:19,813
Patty, um...

1582
01:25:22,753 --> 01:25:26,416
I know, um...

1583
01:25:26,490 --> 01:25:28,822
um...

1584
01:25:32,963 --> 01:25:34,658
um...

1585
01:25:34,731 --> 01:25:37,723
Go on. You can go.

1586
01:25:37,801 --> 01:25:39,769
Thank you.

1587
01:25:40,771 --> 01:25:42,295
Thank you.

1588
01:25:51,548 --> 01:25:52,845
Ma?

1589
01:25:52,916 --> 01:25:54,679
Up here.

1590
01:26:02,859 --> 01:26:03,985
Where's Nino and Joey?

1591
01:26:04,060 --> 01:26:06,028
They're okay.
They're in their room.

1592
01:26:06,096 --> 01:26:07,188
Go get them ready.

1593
01:26:21,077 --> 01:26:22,101
Where you been?

1594
01:26:22,179 --> 01:26:24,773
I went to see Sal.

1595
01:26:24,848 --> 01:26:26,577
And what happened?

1596
01:26:26,650 --> 01:26:28,117
We made a deal.

1597
01:26:28,185 --> 01:26:31,245
He won't kill you if you stay
away from me and my family.

1598
01:26:35,425 --> 01:26:36,357
Um, I don't understand.

1599
01:26:36,426 --> 01:26:39,293
What does...
What does that mean?

1600
01:26:39,362 --> 01:26:43,059
It means it's over. And I get out.

1601
01:26:48,872 --> 01:26:50,897
I won't be needing this anymore.

1602
01:26:51,908 --> 01:26:53,239
Patty...

1603
01:26:58,782 --> 01:27:00,443
Good-bye, Frank.

1604
01:27:07,791 --> 01:27:10,726
<i>True to his word,
Palmeri called off the hit.</i>

1605
01:27:10,794 --> 01:27:14,252
<i>Frank, who expected to go out
in a blaze of fire,</i>

1606
01:27:14,331 --> 01:27:17,027
<i>died three years
later of colon cancer.</i>

1607
01:27:17,100 --> 01:27:18,692
<i>In spite of the
shortage of witnesses,</i>

1608
01:27:18,768 --> 01:27:21,737
<i>Salvatore Palmeri
was sentenced to life in prison</i>

1609
01:27:21,805 --> 01:27:24,296
<i>for ordering the murder of Mouse.</i>

1610
01:27:24,374 --> 01:27:28,174
<i>Pretty soon,
most of the guys we grew up with</i>

1611
01:27:28,245 --> 01:27:32,841
<i>were either locked up or dead.</i>

1612
01:27:32,916 --> 01:27:37,580
<i>Agent Robert Wilford was promoted.
So was Bones...</i>

1613
01:27:37,654 --> 01:27:39,519
<i>an undercover agent the whole time.</i>

1614
01:27:42,759 --> 01:27:45,057
<i>June OD'd.</i>

1615
01:27:45,128 --> 01:27:48,393
<i>Accidental or not, nobody knows.</i>

1616
01:27:48,465 --> 01:27:51,923
<i>Ma did okay, considering.</i>

1617
01:27:52,002 --> 01:27:54,470
<i>Sunliner Express now
boarding on track 8</i>

1618
01:27:54,538 --> 01:27:56,165
<i>for Orlando and Miami.</i>

1619
01:27:58,375 --> 01:28:02,835
<i>My mother, she taught me
everything I know:</i>

1620
01:28:02,913 --> 01:28:06,405
<i>How to think for myself,
how to question authority</i>

1621
01:28:06,483 --> 01:28:08,678
<i>and most important,
how to say no...</i>

1622
01:28:08,752 --> 01:28:12,381
<i>because when the Devil shows up
with a truckload of promises,</i>

1623
01:28:12,455 --> 01:28:16,084
<i>it's harder than you think
to walk away.</i>

1624
01:28:46,085 --> 01:28:47,085
Subtitles by LeapinLar

